Title: "Homecoming"Transcription: "Kikyō" (Japanese: 帰郷)
description: Naruto returns to Konoha after a two-and-a-half-year training journey with Jiraiya and is reunited with Sakura.

Title: "The Akatsuki Makes Its Move"Transcription: "Akatsuki, Shidō" (Japanese: 暁, 始動)
description: Kakashi gives Naruto and Sakura a test to see how far they had improved. Meanwhile, two Akatsuki members, Deidara and Sasori, arrive at the entrance of the Sunagakure to capture the One-Tailed Shukaku's host, Gaara.

Title: "The Results of Training"Transcription: "Shugyō no Seika" (Japanese: 修業の成果)
description: Sakura and Naruto both demonstrate their newly acquired skills. Meanwhile, Deidara commences his attack on Sunagakure and is confronted by Gaara.

Title: "The Jinchuriki of the Sand"Transcription: "Suna no Jinchūriki" (Japanese: 砂の人柱力)
description: Gaara is quick to detect Deidara's presence, and an aerial battle ensues with Deidara on his giant bird and Gaara atop sand.

Title: "The Kazekage Stands Tall"Transcription: "Kazekage to shite...!" (Japanese: 風影として...!)
description: Naruto and Sakura defeat Kakashi in the survival challenge. Tsunade assigns them to a three-man squad led by Kakashi, who tells them they are now his equals.

Title: "Mission Cleared"Transcription: "Norumakuriā" (Japanese: ノルマクリアー)
description: In order to protect his village from Deidara's explosive clay, Gaara uses his chakra to create a giant sand shield.

Title: "Run, Kankuro"Transcription: "Hashire Kankurō" (Japanese: .mw-parser-output ruby>rt{font-feature-settings:"ruby"1;font-size:85%}.mw-parser-output ruby.large{font-size:250%}.mw-parser-output ruby.large>rt{font-size:50%}疾走（はし）れカンクロウ)
description: Gaara, his strength completely exhausted, is whisked away by Deidara. Kankuro ignores Baki's efforts to stop him and immediately sets out in pursuit with a platoon to rescue Gaara.

Title: "Team Kakashi, Deployed"Transcription: "Shutsugeki, Kakashi-han" (Japanese: 出撃, カカシ班)
description: On her way to the Sand Village, Temari encounters Kakashi and his team. Kakashi admonishes Naruto when he tries to rush ahead...

Title: "The Jinchuriki's Tears"Transcription: "Jinchūriki no Namida" (Japanese: 人柱力の涙)
description: An urgent message from the Sand Village detailing the Akatsuki's kidnapping of the Kazekage reaches the Hidden Leaf Village. Tsunade wastes no time in ordering Team Kakashi to the Sand Village.

Title: "Sealing Technique: Phantom Dragons Nine Consuming Seals"Transcription: "Fūin Jutsu: Genryū Kyū Fūjin" (Japanese: 封印術·幻龍九封尽)
description: The Sand ninja fight against time to treat Kankuro. Even the Sand's poison expert, Granny Chiyo, is baffled. The only hope lies with the reinforcements sent by Tsunade.

Title: "The Medical Ninja's Student"Transcription: "Iryō Ninja no Deshi" (Japanese: 医療忍者の弟子)
description: Sakura treats a critically ill Kankuro. After extensive training she's now a full-fledged Medic Ninja, and Sakura amazes everyone with her sure, steady hands.

Title: "The Retired Granny's Determination"Transcription: "Inkyo Babā no Ketsui" (Japanese: 隠居ババアの決意)
description: Pakkun finds the hideout of the Akatsuki. Team Kakashi and Temari prepare to set out to get Gaara back, but Temari is ordered to stay behind and help guard the village.

Title: "A Meeting With Destiny"Transcription: "Innen Aimamieru" (Japanese: 因縁あいまみえる)
description: Team Kakashi encounter Itachi Uchiha, who had dealt them a bitter defeat in the past. Kakashi warns everyone not to look into Itachi's Sharingan Eyes.

Title: "Naruto's Growth"Transcription: "Naruto no Seichō" (Japanese: ナルトの成長)
description: Guy prepares to use a forbidden secret jutsu. Meanwhile, Naruto falls under Itachi's genjutsu, and all the anti-genjutsu training he underwent with Jiraiya races through Naruto's mind.

Title: "The Secret Weapon is Called...."Transcription: "Kakushidama Nazukete" (Japanese: 隠し玉 名付けて...!)
description: Granny Chiyo and Sakura rescue Naruto from Itachi's genjutsu. Without a moment's delay, Kakashi begins a counterattack.

Title: "The Secret of Jinchuriki"Transcription: "Jinchūriki no Himitsu" (Japanese: 人柱力の秘密)
description: Chiyo and Kakashi realize that the attack was just a diversion, and that the Akatsuki have already begun the process of extracting the Tailed Beast from Gaara. Granny Chiyo explains to Naruto and Sakura the connection between the Tailed Beast and the JinchÃ»riki...

Title: "The Death of Gaara!"Transcription: "Gaara Shisu!" (Japanese: 我愛羅死す!)
description: Teams Kakashi and Guy take a short rest. Granny Chiyo watches Naruto dozing off and is reminded of Sasori as a child. The pursuit resumes, and when Chiyo wonders why Naruto puts such effort into rescuing Gaara...

Title: "Charge Tactic! Button Hook Entry!!"Transcription: "Totsunyū! Botan Fukku Entorī" (Japanese: 突入!ボタンフックエントリー)
description: Teams Kakashi and Guy reach the Akatsuki hideout. They hurry to infiltrate but are thwarted by a five-seal barrier. The only way to break the barrier is to remove all five seals at once.

Title: "Traps Activate! Team Guy's Enemy"Transcription: "Torappu Sadō! Gai-han no Teki" (Japanese: 罠（トラップ）作動!ガイ班の敵)
description: Breaking the five-seal barrier set off a trap, which now has Team Guy battling amazingly accurate copies of themselves. Back at the Akatsuki hideout, Deidara and Sasori struggle to take the Nine-Tail Jinchuuriki.

Title: "Hiruko vs. Two Kunoichi!"Transcription: "Hiruko vs. Futari no Kunoichi" (Japanese: ヒルコVS二人の女忍者（くノいち）)
description: At last, the showdown between the old woman and her grandson begins. Sakura is confused by Sasori's strange appearance, and Granny Chiyo explains that this is Hiruko...

Title: "Sasori's Real Face"Transcription: "Sasori no Sugao" (Japanese: サソリの素顔)
description: Granny Chiyo and Sakura manage to expose Sasori, who amazingly looks no older than he did twenty years earlier. Chiyo is even more shocked at the second puppet that Sasori produces.

Title: "Chiyo's Secret Skills"Transcription: "Chiyo no Oku no Te" (Japanese: チヨの奥の手)
description: Sakura is caught by Sasori's tactic and surrounded by a poison cloud. But she uses a Paper Bomb to blow herself free from the poisonous fumes.

Title: "Father and Mother"Transcription: ""Chichi" to "Haha"" (Japanese: 「父」と「母」)
description: The greatest advantage of the puppets created from humans is that one can take over the jutsu that the human used while alive. Hence, the puppet of the Third Kazekage has the special ability to convert chakra into magnetic power. Chiyo and Sakura take cover, and Sasori wastes no time unleashing a ruthless attack. Chiyo fights back to protect Sakura, but in an instant the Father and Mother puppets are sealed by the Iron Sand. As Sasori rushes in for the final blow, Sakura makes a decision.

Title: "The Third Kazekage"Transcription: "Sandaime Kazekage" (Japanese: 三代目風影)
description: Sakura and Chiyo continue their battle with Sasori, while Naruto and Kakashi follow Deidara, and Team Guy fights their clones. Sakura remembers her training with Tsunade when she was taught to observe enemies' weaknesses and dodge their attacks. Sasori attacks with an Iron Sand pyramid and prism, but Sakura is able to fend them off, causing a cave in. Sasori then uses a new technique to attack with randomly-growing iron spikes, landing a hit imbued with a poison that quickly paralyzes its victims. With a final attack of the Third Kazekage's puppet, Sasori attempts to ...

Title: "Three Minutes Between Life and Death"Transcription: "Sei to Shi no Sanpunkan" (Japanese: 生と死の三分間)
description: Sakura reveals that she took an antidote against Sasori's poison which will make her immune to it for three minutes, forcing herself and Chiyo to end the battle quickly. Meanwhile, Naruto and Kakashi continue their pursuit of Deidara. Deidara attempts to split up Naruto and Kakashi by creating a swarm of explosive jumping crickets out of his clay and has them pursue Kakashi. Kakashi makes a shadow clone as a decoy and the crickets, mistaking the shadow clone for the real Kakashi, detonate harmlessly. Kakashi then catches back up with Naruto and reveals a plan. Sakura ...

Title: "Puppet Fight: 10 vs. 100!"Transcription: "Jukki vs Hyakki" (Japanese: 十機vs百機)
description: Naruto and Kakashi continue to pursue Deidara while Sakura and Chiyo continue the battle with Sasori. Sakura manages to shatter Sasori's puppet body, but he reforms. Chiyo summons the Ten Puppets of Chikamatsu. Sasori, remarking on Chiyo's ability to control so many puppets, summons one hundred human puppets and the final battle begins. Sakura and Chiyo seem to trap and defeat Sasori but, under cover of the battle, Sasori, who had transferred himself to another puppet, attacks Chiyo from behind. Sakura intercedes, taking the sword thrust meant for Chiyo.

Title: "Impossible Dream"Transcription: "Kanawanu Yume" (Japanese: 叶わぬ夢)
description: Chiyo injects the last remaining antidote into Sakura and manages to stab Sasori in his only living part, his heart, using the Father and Mother puppets. With Sasori immobilized, Chiyo revives the nearly dead Sakura using her Resurrection Technique. As he dies, Sasori rewards Sakura for defeating him, telling her where he planned to meet with one of his spies who had been working undercover as one of Orochimaru's subordinates. Meanwhile as Kakashi and Naruto are pursuing Deidara, Kakashi reveals his plan to activate his version of Mangekyo Sharingan.

Title: "Beasts: Alive Again!"Transcription: "Yomigaeru Kemono-tachi" (Japanese: 蘇る獣たち)
description: Team Guy senses the result of the Sakura and Granny Chiyo's desperate struggle while still in battle with his deadly copy. Although Guy's team members are showing fatigue, their copies remain strong!

Title: "Kakashi Enlightened!"Transcription: "Kakashi Kaigan!" (Japanese: カカシ開眼!)
description: Sakura hurries to get to Naruto with Granny Chiyo, who is suffering from the poison. The members of Team Guy rush to assist Team Kakashi.

Title: "Aesthetics of an Instant"Transcription: "Shunkan no Bigaku" (Japanese: 瞬間の美学)
description: Naruto loses all reason to anger and is gradually taken over by the Nine-Tailed Fox Spirit. Having been forewarned by Jiraiya, Kakashi narrowly manages to suppress the Nine-Tailed Fox.

Title: "The Legacy"Transcription: "Tsugareyukumono" (Japanese: 継がれゆくもの)
description: Relying on Naruto's power, Granny Chiyo performs the Transmigration Jutsu on Gaara. Sakura is saddened when she realizes the cost of this jutsu.

Title: "Return of the Kazekage"Transcription: "Kazekage no Kikan" (Japanese: 風影の帰還)
description: Deidara survives his battle and begins to search for his missing arm. Meanwhile, Zetsu and his subordinate, Tobi, who wishes to join Akatsuki, search Sasori's remains for his ring. Deidara later finds the two searching for his own ring. The leaf ninja leave Sunagakure after their victory, and Danzo gives Sai instructions for his new team, Team Kakashi. The leaf and sand ninja pay their respects at Chiyo's grave, and Gaara and Naruto shake hands before departing.

Title: "The New Target"Transcription: "Aratanaru Tāgetto" (Japanese: 新たなる目標（ターゲット）)
description: Everyone has returned to the Hidden Leaf Village. Kakashi is hospitalized for a week due to the strain caused by his Mangekyo Sharingan.

Title: "Formation! New Team Kakashi!"Transcription: "Kessei! Shin Kakashi han" (Japanese: 結成!新カカシ班)
description: Naruto, Choji and Shikamaru attempt to capture and interrogate Sai, but Sai withdraws after insulting Naruto. Shortly afterward, Ino appears. Concerned that the demon fox could fall into Akatsuki hands, the village elders challenge Tsunade's plan to send Naruto out of the village without the still bedridden Kakashi. Tsunade promises to protect Konoha with her own life if Naruto is captured, but is still forced to compromise with Danzo by adding Sai to Team Kakashi. She also temporarily replaces Kakashi with ANBU member Yamato and warns him to keep an eye on Sai. ...

Title: "An Unnecessary Addition"Transcription: "Gadatensoku" (Japanese: 画蛇添足（がだてんそく）)
description: Yamato takes temporary leadership of Team Kakashi while Sai insults both Naruto and Sakura. While preparing to set off, Sai receives an envelope from a Root shinobi containing secret orders from Danzo, and Sakura consults with Tsunade. Jiraiya then meets with Tsunade and Yamato in Kakashi's hospital room to brief Yamato on the demon fox within Naruto, detailing the "demon fox's cloak", and revealing a scar he got from Naruto when the fourth tail formed. Finally the new Team Kakashi set off on their new mission, to intercept an Akatsuki spy and gather information about...

Title: "The Fake Smile"Transcription: "Itsuwari no egao" (Japanese: 偽りの笑顔)
description: The new Team Kakashi heads for Tenchikyo. To Naruto, Sai is just temporarily filling in for Sasuke. When Sai shows his contempt for Sasuke, the antagonism comes to a head.

Title: "Untitled"Transcription: "Mudai" (Japanese: 無題)
description: Sakura comes across Sai working on an abstract painting. He tells her that he's unable to give it a title. Bothered by his manner, Sakura finds an unusual picture book among Sai's things.

Title: "Simulation"Transcription: "Shimyurēshon" (Japanese: 模擬戦闘訓練（シミュレーション）)
description: In preparation for Tenchikyo, Yamato conducts a half-day simulation in order to get a grasp on the fighting skills and jutsu of Team Kakashi. Sai abandons Naruto to conclude the simulated mission successfully.

Title: "The Tenchi Bridge"Transcription: "Tenchikyō" (Japanese: 天地橋)
description: The day for capturing the spy is finally here. Just as planned, Yamato takes on Sasori's likeness and waits until the Akatsuki spy appears. The spy turns out to be none other than Kabuto.

Title: "The Nine-Tails Unleashed"Transcription: "Kyūbi kaihō!!" (Japanese: 九尾解放!!)
description: Faced with Orochimaru, his sworn enemy, Naruto suddenly releases the power of his Nine-Tailed Fox. When Yamato sees Naruto's fourth tail appear, he recalls Jiraiya's tale of how he nearly lost his life to the transformed Naruto. Yamato has been ordered to suppress the Nine-Tail chakra that would adversely affect Naruto's body. Then, the secret of Yamato's Wood-Style ninjutsu becomes apparent.

Title: "The Top-Secret Mission Begins"Transcription: "Gokuhi ninmu sutāto" (Japanese: 極秘任務スタート)
description: When his third tail appears, all that Naruto can see is Orochimaru. He is blind even to his teammates.

Title: "Orochimaru vs. Jinchuriki"Transcription: "Orochimaru tai Jinchūriki" (Japanese: 大蛇丸VS人柱力)
description: With the release of his fourth tail, Naruto completely loses his awareness and is overtaken by destructive impulses.

Title: "Sakura's Tears"Transcription: "Sakura no namida" (Japanese: サクラの涙)
description: Although he has changed almost completely into his animal form and has lost all awareness, Naruto refuses to give up the idea of bringing Sasuke home.

Title: "The Secret of the Battle!"Transcription: "Tatakai no tenmatsu" (Japanese: 戦いの顛末)
description: Taking advantage of the confusion, Sai makes contact with Orochimaru. After reviewing the contents of the documents given to him, Orochimaru decides to take Sai back to the hideout.

Title: "The Consequences of Betrayal"Transcription: "Uragiri no hate" (Japanese: 裏切りの果て)
description: Naruto and Sakura are shocked when they hear that Danzo's goal is to work with Orochimaru to once again attempt to defeat the Leaf Village.

Title: "The Unfinished Page"Transcription: "Mikan no Pēji" (Japanese: 未完の頁（ページ）)
description: Naruto is shocked to learn that he was the one responsible for the destruction around them and for Sakura's injuries.

Title: "Infiltration: The Den of the Snake!"Transcription: "Sennyū! Dokuhebi no ajito" (Japanese: 潜入!毒蛇の巣窟（アジト）)
description: Sai shudders when he finally meets Sasuke face to face in Orochimaru's hideout. The list that Sai gave to Orochimaru lists the members of the Anbu Black Ops, the corps under the direct control of the Hokage.

Title: "Bonds"Transcription: "Tsunagari" (Japanese: つながり)
description: Team Kakashi is able to find Sai with Yamato guiding them. They immediately begin questioning Sai about Danzo's plans for destroying the Leaf Village, and surprisingly, Sai divulges everything.

Title: "Something Important..."Transcription: "Taisetsu na mono" (Japanese: 大切なモノ)
description: Kabuto carries out a surprise attack on Team Kakashi to take back Sai, but a change has come over Sai since Sakura pointed out his contradictions.

Title: "The Picture Book's Story"Transcription: "Ehon ga kataru Sutōri" (Japanese: 絵本が語る物語（ストーリー）)
description: Naruto, while nursing his injuries caused by the release of the Nine-Tailed Fox, searches frantically for Sasuke. Seeing this, Sai recalls the feelings he once had for his older brother and finally manages to complete his unfinished picture.

Title: "Reunion"Transcription: "Saikai" (Japanese: 再会)
description: Team Kakashi are stunned to learn that Sai's true mission is to kill Sasuke. Naruto wants to believe that the smile Sai showed them was real, but there is a possibility that it was all an act.

Title: "The Power of Uchiha"Transcription: "Uchiha no chikara" (Japanese: うちはの力)
description: Team Kakashi finally have their wish to be reunited with Sasuke granted. Although it has been three long years, Sasuke's feelings have not changed. His ultimate goal is to get revenge against his older brother, Itachi.

Title: "Title"Transcription: "Taitoru" (Japanese: 題名（タイトル）)
description: Sasuke's desire for revenge remains firm, no matter how hard Naruto tries to talk him out of it. Yamato tries to take Sasuke by force, but interference by Orochimaru brings things to a quick close.

Title: "Nightmare"Transcription: "Akumu" (Japanese: 悪夢)
description: Naruto's been having nightmares about a mysterious person releasing the Nine-Tail's power. After remembering their recent encounter with Sasuke, Naruto realizes that he must get stronger. Meanwhile, Sai tries to adapt to everyday life with Naruto and Sakura. When the group goes to visit Kakashi to discuss the situation, Kakashi lets Naruto know that he has special training for him that will make him stronger, fast. They are joined by Team 10, who have also come to visit.

Title: "Wind"Transcription: "Kaze" (Japanese: 旋風（かぜ）)
description: Naruto begins to train with Kakashi. Kakashi finds it exhausting working with Naruto, who can't understand anything explained to him.

Title: "Squirm"Transcription: "Ugomeku" (Japanese: うごめく)
description: Learning that his chakra is of the "wind" type that is outstanding for fighting, Naruto puts more effort into his training.

Title: "Deprived of Eternal Sleep"Transcription: "Ubawareta nemuri" (Japanese: 奪われた永眠り)
description: Team Kakashi is ordered to resolve the frequent vandalizing of graves at the Fire Temple. When it becomes clear that the vandals aren't after the possessions buried with the dead, Yamato suspects that they want the corpses of the ninja buried in the four hidden tombs near Fire Temple.

Title: "Loneliness"Transcription: "Kodoku" (Japanese: 孤独)
description: At the Fire Temple, Chiriku explains to Team Kakashi that the hidden tombs hold the guards of the Land of Fire's feudal lord. At one time Chiriku and Asuma were members of that organization. Team Kakashi learn about a terrible incident caused by the Twelve Ninja Guardians. Meanwhile, as Naruto watches the young monks training, he notices a strain in the relations between Sora and the other monks.

Title: "A New Enemy"Transcription: "Aratana teki" (Japanese: 新たな敵)
description: Word comes that the last of the hidden graves has been broken into. Naruto and the others go after the coffin, but it turns out to be a trap.

Title: "Impermanence"Transcription: "Uitenpen" (Japanese: 有為転変)
description: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

Title: "Contact"Transcription: "Sesshoku" (Japanese: 接触)
description: Sora confronts Furido, the mysterious figure who has broken into the hidden graves. Impressed by Sora's unusual strength, he admonishes him, "You should reevaluate how you use that power Heaven has blessed you with," and disappears, leaving him with a cryptic message that he is an old friend of his father.

Title: "Teammate"Transcription: "Chīmumeito" (Japanese: チームメイト)
description: Yamato believes that the assailants were not grave robbers but were after Sora. He decides to appoint Sora to Team Kakashi as a temporary stand-in for the injured Sai.

Title: "The Two Kings"Transcription: "Futatsu no gyoku" (Japanese: 二つの玉（ぎょく）)
description: Asuma supervises Naruto and Sora's wind chakra training, and notices that Sora, like Naruto, has very powerful chakra. Tsunade and Yamato learn from Chiriku that Sora was inadvertently responsible for an incident in which the Temple of Fire was destroyed. Later, Asuma gives Sora a claw made from the same materials as his chakra blades. It is revealed that Asuma killed Sora's father Kazuma, who had planned to kill the Hokage. Furido then approaches Sora, telling him that Asuma is responsible for his father's death and passing him two "king" pieces from a Shogi set for ...

Title: "Jet Black Signal Fire"Transcription: "Shikkoku no noroshi" (Japanese: 漆黒の狼煙)
description: Danzou is brought in for questioning after being caught meeting with a young Rain ninja. Sora confronts Asuma, and Asuma admits to having killed Kazuma. He attacks Asuma, his arm once again assuming a demonic form. Afterward, Naruto gets injured while shielding Sora from the attacks of an unknown individual, presumably from Root. Furido then approaches Sora, telling him to kill both Asuma and the Hokage to avenge his father. Later on, Naruto catches Sora going after Tsunade. Sora retreats as Shizune and a few other ninja arrive, but Naruto pursues him. At that moment,...

Title: "Lockdown of Darkness"Transcription: "Ankoku no sejō" (Japanese: 暗黒の施錠)
description: Under cover of a giant power outage, Furido begins his assault on the Hidden Leaf. The village immediately goes on alert, but Furido's men put up a barrier, and everyone in the village is trapped inside. Naruto and Asuma finally catch up to Sora, who is planning an escape in the midst of the panic. He explodes with anger at Naruto's demand to know why he attacked Tsunade. But Asuma is quick to suspect that there is someone behind Sora, someone who knows about the coup d'état incident involving two groups within the Guardian Shinobi Twelve, and realizes that the ...

Title: "Revived Souls"Transcription: "Yomigaeru tamashii" (Japanese: 黄泉がえる魂)
description: In order to stop the impending disaster, Asuma rushes toward the electric generator system. There he sees the Guardian Shinobi Twelve who have come to life once more through Revival Jutsu after their graves were robbed.

Title: "Everyone's Struggle to the Death"Transcription: "Sorezore no shitō" (Japanese: それぞれの死闘)
description: Sora refuses to let Furido destroy the village despite his grudge against Asuma and the Hokage. He is beaten up by Furido, who claims that his father had a similar flaw. Asuma gets trapped by Kitane in a force field of lightning. Meanwhile, Yamato and Sakura kill their opponents, and Shikamaru heads to the battlefield with a plan to defeat the zombies. Just as he puts it into motion, however, Fuen's barrier falls and Fudo's revival technique ends, and the zombies turn to dust.

Title: "Moment of Awakening"Transcription: "Mezame no toki" (Japanese: 覚醒（めざ）めの刻（とき）)
description: Naruto deduces that Fuuka's secret consists of switching bodies to use each corresponding element and that her hair preserves her youth and body. Naruto damages her hair and it takes a life of its own dispensing the body, but Naruto finally kills it with a Rasengan. Meanwhile, Asuma manages to break free of the electric barrier, catch up with Kitane and defeat him in a short fight. Realizing that Kitane is no more, and that his three other companions were killed, Furido causes the 3 other ninja guardians to disappear. But Furido has a back up plan, Sora.

Title: "Despair"Transcription: "Zetsubō" (Japanese: 絶望)
description: Naruto and Asuma catch up to Sora, only to find him shrouded in ominous chakra and undergoing a change.

Title: "Resonance"Transcription: "Kyōmei" (Japanese: 共鳴)
description: Furido's true form belongs to Kazuma, one of the Guardian Shinobi Twelve who had planned the coup d'Ã©tat. Asuma puts his honor on the line and goes back ten years to battle Furido once more.

Title: "My Friend"Transcription: "Tomo yo" (Japanese: 友よ)
description: The struggle between Naruto and Sora continues. Asuma and Kazuma fight. Sai arrives, having sneaked out of hospital, and binds Kazuma with an ink snake. Kazuma breaks out of Sai's jutsu and charges Asuma, but is killed. Naruto eventually reaches Sora, who manages to release the Nine Tails's chakra. Sora then leaves the village to travel the world. Asuma and Shikamaru play shogi and discuss who the king of Konoha is. Elsewhere, two Akatsuki members, Hidan and Kakuzu, appear chasing the Two Tails Jinchuuriki.

Title: "The Quietly Approaching Threat"Transcription: "Shinobiyoru kyōi" (Japanese: 忍び寄る脅威)
description: Work continues in Hidden Leaf Village to erase the scars of battle. As he watches Konohamaru and the others helping with the reconstruction, Iruka sees how his students have matured.

Title: "Akatsuki's Invasion"Transcription: "Akatsuki shinkō" (Japanese: “暁”侵攻)
description: With Kakashi's return, Naruto resumes training for his new jutsu. Kakashi explains that the transformation training will enter the next stage. This time, only Wind Chakra will be used to cut through a waterfall. Hidan and Kakuzu, who have captured Two Tails, leave it with Zetsu and head for the Land of Fire in search of Nine Tails. The first place they reach is the Fire Temple, where the priests go into a near panic, and Chiriku confronts the Akatsuki.

Title: "Under the Starry Sky"Transcription: "Hoshizora no moto de" (Japanese: 星空の下（もと）で)
description: The lone surviving priest is carried into Hidden Leaf Village where he reports the destruction of the Fire Temple.

Title: "The Old Monk's Prayer"Transcription: "Rōsō no inori" (Japanese: 老僧の祈り)
description: In order to capture the Akatsuki, the Hidden Leaf cast a net that even an ant could not crawl through. Still, the Akatsuki elude them and frustrate Tsunade to no end. Around that time, Asuma and the others arrive at the Fire Temple, only to find it completely destroyed. Chiriku's corpse is missing, and Asuma surmises that the Akatsuki were after the bounty on Chiriku's head. They immediately dispatch a messenger to Hidden Leaf to submit a report and head for the nearest center where the Akatsuki can turn in Chiriku's body for payment. Back at Hidden Leaf, Naruto takes...

Title: "The Next Step"Transcription: "Tsuginaru Suteppu" (Japanese: 次なる階段（ステップ）)
description: Naruto is learning the elements of Wind Style Jutsu, and Kakashi lectures him on the difficulties of developing a new jutsu. According to Kakashi even the Fourth Hokage was not able to embed elemental chakra into his jutsu. Naruto feels a heavy sense of responsibility and puts his entire being into developing the new jutsu. Meanwhile, the Akatsuki duo turns in Chiriku's body to collect the bounty. What is the fate of the Hidden Leaf team who are pursuing them...?

Title: "Climbing Silver"Transcription: "Bōgin" (Japanese: 棒銀)
description: Asuma and his team finally confront Hidan, and a battle ensues. They fight with all their strength but are shocked at Hidan's power.

Title: "The Judgment"Transcription: "Kudasareta sabaki" (Japanese: 下された裁き)
description: Hidan releases a baffling jutsu, and Asuma bears the brunt of the attack. The jutsu is a special trick which links Hidan with Asuma's body.

Title: "Unfulfilled Scream"Transcription: "Todokanu zekkyō" (Japanese: 届かぬ絶叫)
description: Hidan's immortality enables him to stay alive even with his head cut off, although he cannot move his body. Kakuzu sews Hidan's head back on with threads that sprout from his body. Izumo and Kotetsu try to attack Kakuzu, but he manages to grab them both by using his body threads, restraining them and suffocating them as well. Hidan, now able to move again, returns to the circle and stabs himself with the blades of his scythe; he finishes it off by stabbing himself in the chest with another spike, fatally wounding Asuma.

Title: "Last Words"Transcription: "Saigo no kotoba" (Japanese: 最期の言葉)
description: Asuma is mortally wounded by Hidan's jutsu, and the Akatsuki have the rest of the Hidden Leaf in a bind.

Title: "Sad News"Transcription: "Kanashiki shirase" (Japanese: 悲しき報せ)
description: In a faraway land, the Akatsuki reveal their true aim of world conquest. And back at Hidden Leaf Village, Shikamaru gives his report of the mission to Tsunade.

Title: "Team Ten"Transcription: "Daijuppan" (Japanese: 第十班)
description: Asuma's funeral is held in Hidden Leaf Village amid deep sadness. Shikamaru is the lone absentee, unable to get over the loss.

Title: "Target: Locked On"Transcription: "Tāgetto Rokkuon" (Japanese: 標的捕捉（ターゲット・ロックオン）)
description: Kakashi and Team 10 set out to stop the Akatsuki. Tsunade considers Naruto's Team 7 to be the ideal back-up for Team 10 and orders Naruto to perfect his new jutsu within 24 hours.

Title: "Kakuzu's Abilities"Transcription: "Kakuzu no nōryoku" (Japanese: 角都の能力)
description: Shikamaru and Choji deliver the first blows in the battle, but they are thwarted by Kakuzu's power. Kakashi counters Kakuzu's trick and brings him down.

Title: "The Terrifying Secret"Transcription: "Osorubeki himitsu" (Japanese: 恐るべき秘密)
description: Shikamaru and his comrades desperately counter the Fire Jutsu offensive. But continuously using his Rasengan and Lightning Blade takes its toll on Kakashi.

Title: "Shikamaru's Genius"Transcription: "Shikamaru no Sai" (Japanese: シカマルの才)
description: Shikamaru battles Hidan alone, deep in the forest, and after depleting his chakra, sustains a deep wound. Hidan draws his blood as he lies near death.

Title: "When You Curse Someone, You Dig Your Own Grave"Transcription: "Hito o norowaba ana futatsu" (Japanese: 人を呪わば穴二つ)
description: Naruto and Team Kakashi arrive just in time to assist Team Asuma. Sakura and Sai are ordered by Kakashi to aid Shikamaru, who is battling alone.

Title: "Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken!"Transcription: "Fūton: Rasenshuriken!" (Japanese: 風遁·螺旋手裏剣!)
description: Ino and Choji are amazed at Naruto's new jutsu, and Kakuzu senses the danger that it poses. But when released, the new jutsu dissipates before it reaches Kakuzu.

Title: "The Price of Power"Transcription: "Chikara no daishō" (Japanese: 力の代償)
description: Naruto's uses his new jutsu to bring Kakuzu down. Tsunade welcomes the teams back home and orders Team Asuma and Team Yamato to take a break.

Title: "A Shinobi's Determination"Transcription: "Shinobi no ketsui" (Japanese: 忍の決意)
description: Just when peace has finally settled over the village word comes that Orochimaru's hideout has been found. Tsunade orders Kakashi, Hinata, Shino, and Kiba on a search mission to find the hideout.

Title: "Orochimaru's Hideout Discovered"Transcription: "Hakken — Orochimaru no ajito" (Japanese: 発見 大蛇丸のアジト)
description: Naruto and Jiraiya arrive at the hot springs resort. As an alternative to the Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken, Jiraiya suggests to Naruto the collaboration ninjutsu with a ninja toad.

Title: "Encounter"Transcription: "Deai" (Japanese: 遭遇（であい）)
description: Inside Orochimaru's hideout Guren witnesses Sasuke defeating a thousand opponents. Meanwhile, Kabuto and Yukimaru conduct their experiment to summon the Three-Tailed Beast.

Title: "Connecting Hearts"Transcription: "Kayoiau kokoro" (Japanese: 通い合う心)
description: Believing Naruto's new jutsu is almost completed, Jiraiya heads off to investigate new information on the Akatsuki's movements. His arm now healed, Naruto returns to the village to continue his training.

Title: "A Night of Rain"Transcription: "Ame hitoyo" (Japanese: 雨一夜（あめひとよ）)
description: Staying behind at the hideout, Rinji and Gozu become aware of a shinobi following their tracks. At the same time, Kakashi and his team notice that the enemy is using a bat for surveillance.

Title: "The Two Charms"Transcription: "Futatsu no omamori" (Japanese: ふたつのお守り)
description: At the Leaf Village Naruto is busy training with Gamakichi and Gamatatsu. But when he learns that Kakashi and the others are out on a mission to locate Orochimaru's hideout, Naruto rushes to ask Tsunade if he can join the mission.

Title: "The Unseeing Enemy"Transcription: "Miezaru teki" (Japanese: 見えざる敵)
description: Team Yamato heads out to provide backup for Team Kakashi. Right before his departure Naruto gets a hint to perfect his new jutsu by entering Gamatatsu's belly.

Title: "The Labyrinth of Distorted Reflection"Transcription: "Ranhansha no meikyū" (Japanese: 乱反射の迷宮)
description: From the results of the analysis of the crystallized Parasitic insects, the enemies currently fighting Kakashi's team are identified as users of the Crystal Style, a rare type of jutsu. Still unclear on what Orochimaru's objective is, Tsunade cannot hide her irritation and anxiety.

Title: "The Target Appears"Transcription: "Arawareta hyōteki" (Japanese: 現れた標的)
description: Shattering the force field with his newly mastered collaboration jutsu with the toads, Naruto and the reinforcement unit arrive at the battle site. But Naruto's new jutsu is repulsed by Guren's ability to crystallize fluids.

Title: "The Rampaging Tailed Beast"Transcription: "Arekurū Bijū" (Japanese: 荒れ狂う尾獣)
description: The Leaf ninja use The Bat to pursue Guren. Akamaru and Kiba detect a high level of chakra present at their destination. Convinced something abnormal is about to happen, Kakashi sends Naruto to the lake right before entering battle with the enemy.

Title: "Inside the Mist"Transcription: "Kiri no naka de" (Japanese: 霧の中で)
description: Inside the heavy mist, the Leaf ninja manage to rendezvous with Naruto. The team tightens their guard when they learn that the mist surrounding the lake causes illusions. The team discovers that the enemy is after the Three-Tailed Beast, and faced with this unexpected development, Kakashi decides to ask for Tsunade's guidance.

Title: "Everyone's Feelings"Transcription: "Sorezore no omoi" (Japanese: それぞれの想い)
description: Naruto enters the mist to seek out Yukimaru. Guren stays alert to protect Yukimaru, whose current situation prevents him from moving. When both sides meet, their emotion over Yukimaru sparks.

Title: "Regroup!"Transcription: "Saihensei!" (Japanese: 再編成!)
description: Reinforcements arrive from the Leaf Village. The new mission from Tsunade: seal the Three-Tailed Beast so it won't fall into anyone else's hands and take Yukimaru whose powers are tied to the Tailed Beast into custody.

Title: "The Four-Corner Sealing Barrier"Transcription: "Kekkai Shihō Fūjin" (Japanese: 結界四方封陣)
description: The Leaf ninja wish to seal the Three-Tailed Beast, and Guren's team wishes to stop them at any cost. Shizune's sealing team begins their search as they activate the The Four-Corner Sealing Barrier to trap the Three-Tailed Beast...

Title: "Breaking the Crystal Style"Transcription: "Shōton kuzushi" (Japanese: 晶遁崩し)
description: To protect the The Four-Corner Sealing Barrier necessary to seal the Three-Tailed Beast, Kakashi and Naruto wage their deadly battle against Guren. Sai fights a one-on-one battle with Gozu...

Title: "The Battle Over the Barrier"Transcription: "Kekkai kōbōsen" (Japanese: 結界攻防戦)
description: Kabuto plans on breaking the Leaf's The Four-Corner Sealing Barrier from the inside by using Yukimaru's power and have the Three-Tailed Beast go on a rampage.

Title: "Red Camellia"Transcription: "Akai tsubaki" (Japanese: 赤い椿)
description: To protect Guren from the raging Three Tails, Yuukimaru exerts powers beyond his limits. Moved by his action, Guren now comes to regret her past sin of killing Yuukimaru's mother.

Title: "Strange Bedfellows"Transcription: "Goetsudōshū" (Japanese: 呉越同舟)
description: To protect Yuukimaru, Naruto and Guren fight alongside each other against the Three-Tailed beast and are swallowed. Inside the beast is an unnatural world filled with limestone.

Title: "Guidepost of the Camellia"Transcription: "Tsubaki no michishirube" (Japanese: 椿の道標)
description: The Leaf ninja learn that Naruto is inside the Three-Tailed beast. With no other alternative but to trust Yuukimaru's mystical senses, Kakashi and the others follow the boy's guidance and attempt a rescue mission.

Title: "Counterattack of the Curse Mark"Transcription: "Juin no gyakushū" (Japanese: 呪印の逆襲)
description: Despite the Leaf ninja rescue attempt, Naruto and Guren do not return. Frustration builds among the group, but as Three Tails wakes from its sleep, the Sealing Team makes a second attempt at the Four Corner Sealing Barrier.

Title: "Memory of Guilt"Transcription: "Tsumi no kioku" (Japanese: 罪の記憶)
description: Kabuto plots to have Three Tails crush the Leaf ninja by sacrificing Yuukimaru's power and life. Controlled by Yuukimaru, Three Tails' awesome power is about to break free from the seal, when an unexpected ally saves Shizune's sealing team.

Title: "Shattered Promise"Transcription: "Kudakareta yakusoku" (Japanese: 砕かれた約束)
description: Kabuto finally appears before Naruto. Learning that Orochimaru used Guren's and Yuukimaru's feelings for his own purposes, an enraged Naruto enters battle against Kabuto.

Title: "A Place to Return To"Transcription: "Kaerubeki basho" (Japanese: 帰るべき場所)
description: The Leaf ninja fall back and tend to their wounds. The battle has left everyone with serious injuries. Shizune examines Yuukimaru, who is in a coma, but his body is no longer able to control Three Tails.

Title: "The Serpent's Pupil[note 1]"Transcription: "Daija no dōkō" (Japanese: 大蛇の瞳孔)
description: Orochimaru agonizes in pain at his hideout, now requiring level-ten medications just to sustain his body. Even with excruciating pain Orochimaru is preparing for his transference ritual, and Kabuto can feel Orochimaru's further potential.

Title: "Eye of the Hawk"Transcription: "Taka no hitomi" (Japanese: 鷹の瞳)
description: Orochimaru sheds his old body and transforms into a white serpent. As he attacks Sasuke to obtain his body, Orochimaru remembers the time he found the slough of a white snake in front of his parents' grave.

Title: "Zabuza's Blade"Transcription: "Zabuza no daitō" (Japanese: 再不斬の大刀)
description: Sasuke has defeated Orochimaru. He then frees Suigetsu, a man trapped inside a water tank, and tells the man to join him. But Suigetsu does not immediately take up Sasuke's offer...

Title: "Guardian of the Iron Wall"Transcription: "Teppeki no bannin" (Japanese: 鉄壁の番人)
description: Sasuke and Suigetsu visit the southern hideout to recruit their next member, Karin. Suigetsu is surprised at the hideout's low security level but is told that no prisoners can escape thanks to Karin's abilities. What is Karin's power that allows her to maintain order and an iron defense?

Title: "Jugo of the North Hideout"Transcription: "Kita ajito no Jūgo" (Japanese: 北アジトの重吾)
description: Sasuke and his team head for the northern hideout to recruit their next member, Jugo. On the way, Karin explains that the northern hideout is a site for conducting horrific human experiments. A ninja with abnormal homicidal impulses, Jugo is the sole carrier of the enzyme necessary to create Orochimaru's curse mark...

Title: "Formation!"Transcription: "Kessei!" (Japanese: 結成!)
description: Slipping past the riot, Sasuke arrives at Jugo's cell. But Jugo refuses to be released, even going as far as to say he rather die a lonely death than to leave the hideout.

Title: "Kakashi Chronicles ~Boys' Life on the Battlefield~ Part 1"Transcription: "Kakashi Gaiden ~Senjō no bōizuraifu~ Zenpen" (Japanese: カカシ外伝～戦場のボーイズライフ～前編)
description: More than ten years ago, the rule of the Five Great Shinobi Nations was destabilized, throwing the world into a conflict later to be known as the Third Great Ninja War.The future Fourth Hokage Minato Namikaze assigns young Kakashi, Obito of the Uchiha clan, and Rin, a medical ninja, on a mission to Kannabi Bridge...

Title: "Kakashi Chronicles ~Boys' Life on the Battlefield~ Part 2"Transcription: "Kakashi Gaiden ~Senjō no bōizuraifu~ Kōhen" (Japanese: カカシ外伝～戦場のボーイズライフ～後編)
description: Obito ignores Kakashi's order to continue with the mission and leaves to save Rin, who was kidnapped by the Rock ninja. But the enemies detect Obito's arrival and defeat him. Kakashi arrives at the last minute and saves Obito...

Title: "Assemble"Transcription: "Ugokidasumono-tachi" (Japanese: 動き出すものたち)
description: After hunting down the Four Tails, Itachi and Kisame are summoned by the leader of the Akatsuki. The leader announces the death of Orochimaru to the gathered members and the possibility of his killer, Sasuke, setting his sights on the Akatsuki organization....

Title: "The Hunt"Transcription: "Tansaku" (Japanese: 探索)
description: Under Kakashi's command, the Leaf ninja set off to find Itachi. Using Kakashi's ninja hounds, they gather as much information as they can on Itachi. Meanwhile, the members of the Hebi also scatter to look for information on Itachi. Led by the ninja hound tracking Sasuke's scent, Sakura arrives in town and draws near to Karin.

Title: "Clash!"Transcription: "Gekitotsu!" (Japanese: 激突!)
description: Upon encountering one another, Sasuke and Deidara engage in battle. After exchanging a few blows to test Sasuke's strength, Deidara conjures up his specialty clay dragon and wages long-range attacks against Sasuke from high above. With Tobi's backup support, the battle seems to be going to Deidara.

Title: "Art"Transcription: "Geijutsu" (Japanese: 芸術)
description: Determined to destroy the Sharingan to rid himself of the taste of defeat he received from Itachi, Deidara unleashes his biggest attack, the C4 Karura. Created to kill Itachi, this fierce weapon is capable of destroying living beings from the inside using millions of nano-sized bombs. Can Sasuke escape this attack fueled by Deidara's determination to destroy the Sharingan?

Title: "Disappearance"Transcription: "Shōshitsu" (Japanese: 消失)
description: Sasuke goes missing after being caught by Deidara's suicidal bombing. Sensing his disappearance, Jugo, Karin, and Suigetsu race to Sasuke's last location, where the three Hebi members discover...?

Title: "Twilight"Transcription: "Tasogare" (Japanese: 黄昏)
description: Leaf ninja, she notifies the others and the Hebi members quickly leave the inn. To allow Sasuke to focus on his coming battle with Itachi, Karin comes up with a plan to keep the Leaf ninja occupied.

Title: "Tales of a Gutsy Ninja ~Jiraiya Ninja Scroll~ Part 1"Transcription: "Dokonjō ninden ~Jiraiya ninpōchō~ Zenpen" (Japanese: ド根性忍伝～自来也忍法帖～前編)
description: During the reign of the Second Hokage, the young Jiraiya, Orochimaru, and Tsunade are assigned to Hiruzen Sarutobi's platoon as Genins. While training, Jiraiya accidentally transports himself to Mount Myoboku, opening the path to fulfill his destiny.

Title: "Tales of a Gutsy Ninja ~Jiraiya Ninja Scroll~ Part 2"Transcription: "Dokonjō ninden ~Jiraiya ninpōchō~ Kōhen" (Japanese: ド根性忍伝～自来也忍法帖～後編)
description: Jiraiya's journey to seek out a student is postponed due to the outbreak of the Third Great Ninja War. Jiraiya joins Tsunade and Orochimaru to battle the Village Hidden in the Rain.

Title: "Infiltrate! The Village Hidden in the Rain"Transcription: "Sennyū! Amegakure no Sato" (Japanese: 潜入! 雨隠れの里)
description: Jiraiya successfully infiltrates the Hidden Rain Village by hiding inside the toad Gamagoro. He sets out to gather information but finds no indications of a civil war occurring within the village.

Title: "The Man Who Became God"Transcription: "Kami to natta Otoko" (Japanese: 神となった男)
description: Foreseeing a possible battle, Jiraiya takes precautionary measures by storage releasing the scroll toad that commands the key to Naruto's Eight-Signed Seal.

Title: "Honored Sage Mode!"Transcription: "Hatsudō! Sennin Mōdo" (Japanese: 発動! 仙人モード)
description: Jiraiya battles to defeat his former student Pain, who is now driven by his twisted ideals as an Akatsuki member.

Title: "In Attendance, the Six Paths of Pain"Transcription: "Pein Rikudō, kenzan" (Japanese: ペイン六道、見参)
description: Jiraiya completes his Sage Mode transformation to battle the three Pains.

Title: "The Tale of Jiraiya the Gallant"Transcription: "Jiraiya gōketsu monogatari" (Japanese: 自来也豪傑物語)
description: Having lost his arm, Jiraiya is outmatched by the six Pains now appearing before him. Of the six, the one called Tendo is revealed to be Jiraiya's former student Yahiko. Jiraiya is still puzzled by the Rinnegan's true powers, but before he can gather his thoughts, he is forced back into battle.

Title: "Banquet Invitation"Transcription: "Utage e no izanai" (Japanese: 宴への誘い)
description: As Sasuke proceeds to Itachi's hideout, Tobi messes with Naruto.

Title: "The Longest Moment"Transcription: "Nagaki toki no naka de..." (Japanese: 長き瞬間の中で...)
description: While Itachi waits for Sasuke in the Uchiha hideout, he recalls the past incident that led to his defection from the Leaf Village. When Sasuke arrives, the fated battle begins between the two brothers.

Title: "The Light & Dark of the Mangekyo Sharingan"Transcription: "Mangekyō Sharingan no hikari to yami" (Japanese: 万華鏡写輪眼の光と闇)
description: Following their fierce genjutsu battle with the Sharingan, Itachi explains the secret behind the most powerful ocular jutsu, the Mangekyo Sharingan, and the history of the Uchiha clan...

Title: "Amaterasu!" (Japanese: 天照)
description: Sasuke loses his left eye to Itachi, but it turns out to be a genjutsu created by the Mangekyo Sharingan. Breaking free of the Tsukuyomi by force, Sasuke makes a furious comeback against the injured Itachi.

Title: "The End"Transcription: "Shūen" (Japanese: 終焉)
description: At the climax of the battle, both Itachi and Sasuke run out of chakra. However, Sasuke reveals that his actions up until now were only a preparation for his final jutsu.

Title: "The Mystery of Tobi"Transcription: "Tobi no nazo" (Japanese: トビの謎)
description: Naruto and his comrades find themselves held up by Tobi, whose strange jutsu is more than just a simple genjutsu.

Title: "Fate"Transcription: "Innen" (Japanese: 因縁)
description: In the Akatsuki hideout Sasuke comes face to face with Madara. Announcing himself as Itachi's accomplice from that fateful night, Madara goes on to tell Sasuke the truth about Itachi that he could never have known.

Title: "Truth"Transcription: "Shinjitsu" (Japanese: 真実)
description: The Uchiha clan was plotting a coup d'etat. The story as told by Madara leaves Sasuke at a loss for words. Because of his gifted talent, Itachi was forced to suffer, torn between his loyalties to the Leaf Village and the Uchiha clan.

Title: "Battle of Unraikyo"Transcription: "Unraikyō no tatakai" (Japanese: 雲雷峡の闘い)
description: Flame from the Amaterasu still remains on the battlefield as Naruto and his teammates continue to search for Sasuke. But despite the search team's best efforts, they cannot find any trace of him.

Title: "The Eight-Tails vs. Sasuke"Transcription: "Hachibi' tai 'Sasuke" (Japanese: 「八尾」対「サスケ」)
description: The Taka split up with the Akatsuki to hunt down the remaining Tailed Beast. At the Land of Lightning they go up against Killer Bee, whose attack utilizing Lightning Style and seven blades proves to be more than a match for them.

Title: "Wanderer"Transcription: "Fūraibō" (Japanese: 風来坊)
description: The Leaf ninja fail to capture Itachi and also lose track of Sasuke. Calling off their pursuit, the team is heading back to the village when an urgent assignment from Lady Tsunade comes in. The mission stems from a treaty between the Third Hokage and the En no Gyoja of the Tsuchigumo Clan...

Title: "Successor of the Forbidden Jutsu"Transcription: "Kinjutsu no keishōsha" (Japanese: 禁術の継承者)
description: Naruto and his teammates are assigned to escort Hotaru, En no Gyoja's granddaughter, to the Tsuchigumo Clan's village located in the mountains. But Hotaru's mind is still attached to Utakata, who left after Naruto's arrival...

Title: "The Successor's Wish"Transcription: "Keishōsha no omoi" (Japanese: 継承者の想い)
description: Having arrived at the village, Hotaru parts with Naruto and his team. But the Magaki Troops are one step ahead and threaten Hotaru to hand over the forbidden jutsu. Utakata appears, and Shiranami recognizes him as a bounty listed in the Hidden Mist's bingo book...

Title: "Rogue Ninja's Past"Transcription: "Nukenin no kako" (Japanese: 抜け忍の過去)
description: Yamato and Sai recognize their opponents as trackers from the Hidden Mist Village, but Naruto attacks without questioning. The Hidden Mist demands Utakata be handed over to them in exchange for Hotaru.

Title: "Heir to Darkness"Transcription: "Yami no kōkeisha" (Japanese: 闇の後継者)
description: Hotaru is brought back to the fort in Mount Katsuragi. Naruto, outraged to learn the forbidden jutsu was embedded inside Hotaru, demands an explanation from Tonbei. But it was none other than Hotaru herself who wished for this.

Title: "Parting"Transcription: "Betsuri" (Japanese: 別離)
description: Believing Shiranami's story, Hotaru writes a parting letter addressed to Utakata and leaves Mount Katsuragi. Meanwhile Naruto, still searching for Shiranami, falls into the Magaki Troops' trap but manages to escape thanks to help from Utakata.

Title: "The Forbidden Jutsu Released"Transcription: "Kinjutsu hatsudō" (Japanese: 禁術発動)
description: Naruto and Utakata successfully enter the Tsuchigumo village thanks to help from Sakura, Sai, and Yamato. Utakata senses the chakra filling the atmosphere and terrain behaving oddly, and together with Naruto, they enter the cave where the anomaly is originating.

Title: "Master and Student"Transcription: "Shitei" (Japanese: 師弟)
description: Naruto has a strange nightmare several days after their failure to bring Sasuke home. Even after he awakens wisps of the dream keep haunting him.

Title: "Somber News"Transcription: "Hihō" (Japanese: 悲報)
description: Returning from the mission, Naruto recollects his strange encounter with Itachi. What did the now deceased Itachi wish to tell him? As Naruto ponders this, Kakashi makes an abrupt visit.

Title: "Following the Master's Shadow"Transcription: "Shi no Kage o Otte" (Japanese: 師の影を追って)
description: Naruto wanders the streets of the Leaf Village, grief stricken over the death of Jiraiya. Unable to overcome his feeling of loss, Naruto traces back through his memories of Jiraiya. What can help the heartbroken Naruto get back on his feet?

Title: "Decryption"Transcription: "Angō Kaidoku" (Japanese: 暗号解読)
description: Naruto and his friends successfully decipher the code Jiraiya left behind with the help of some information Naruto has. The crew immediately calls Fukasaku over, but the message is not enough to solve the mystery of Pain.

Title: "The First Challenge"Transcription: "Daiichi no Kadai" (Japanese: 第一の課題)
description: At Mount Myoboku, Naruto begins his Sage Jutsu training under Fukasaku. The first challenge is "Don't move." Fukasaku explains that an extensive amount of time is necessary in order to take in nature energy.

Title: "Surpassing the Master"Transcription: "Shi o Koeru Toki" (Japanese: 師を超えるとき)
description: Naruto continues his Sage training at Mount Myoboku, but with very slow progress. Fukasaku runs out of patience and suggests they move on to the next training...

Title: "Assault on the Leaf Village!"Transcription: "Konoha Shūgeki!" (Japanese: 木ノ葉襲撃!)
description: Shikamaru and the others wait for the information Jiraiya brought back to be analyzed. The Hidden Leaf ninja continue their data analysis, when disaster strikes the village

Title: "Power to Believe"Transcription: "Shinjiru Chikara" (Japanese: 信じる力)
description: The Leaf Village is under heavy attack from Pain and Konan. Hearing the Akatsuki attack, Tsunade attempts to contact Fukasaku...

Title: "Pain vs. Kakashi"Transcription: "Pein vs Kakashi" (Japanese: ペインvsカカシ)
description: In one area of the village, Kakashi enters battle against Tendo Pain, but he can't keep up with Tendo's mysterious attacks. Shurado joins the fight, and Kakashi struggles with the two-on-one disadvantage.

Title: "Mystery of Pain"Transcription: "Pein no Nazo" (Japanese: ペインの謎)
description: The Leaf Village is under heavy attack from the Akatsuki. Underneath the village Danzo takes action to achieve his ambition. Meanwhile, searching through the Rain ninja's mind, Inoichi Yamanaka is about to stumble upon valuable information.

Title: "Surname Is Sarutobi. Given Name, Konohamaru!"Transcription: "Sei wa Sarutobi, Na wa Konohamaru!" (Japanese: 姓は猿飛、名は木ノ葉丸!)
description: Konohamaru Sarutobi fights Naraka Pain.

Title: "Pain to the World"Transcription: "Sekai ni Itami o" (Japanese: 世界に痛みを)
description: Tsunade comes face to face with Tendo Pain on the rooftop of the Hokage mansion. When Pain demands the Nine Tails be handed over, Tsunade refuses.

Title: "Explode! Sage Mode"Transcription: "Bakuhatsu! Sennin Mōdo" (Japanese: 爆発! 仙人モード)
description: Sensing danger at hand, Naruto, along with Fukasaku, rushes back to the Leaf Village from Mount Myoboku. But what they see is the remains of the Leaf Village, leveled beyond recognition.

Title: "Danger! Sage Mode Limit Reached"Transcription: "Pinchi! Kieta Sennin Mōdo" (Japanese: 危機! 消えた仙人モード)
description: Naruto hits Pain with his Sage Jutsu-perfected Wind Style Rasen Shuriken. Although he succeeds in defeating Ningendo, the remaining Pain quickly confronts him.

Title: "Nine-Tails, Captured!"Transcription: "Kyūbi Hokaku Kanryō" (Japanese: 九尾捕獲完了)
description: Gamabunta and the other toads are defeated while Naruto is captured by Pain. Naruto attempts to fight back with Sage Jutsu, but Gakido sucks out his chakra, forcing him to go out of Sage Mode. Fukasaku and Shima prepare to activate genjutsu, the same one they used to assist Jiraiya, this time to break the Rinnegan's link. Meanwhile, to not let Shizune's death be in vain, Shikamaru and the other Leaf ninja vow to find the real Pain. As they prepare to gather further information, Inoichi Yamanaka comes to an important realization...

Title: "Confessions"Transcription: "Kokuhaku" (Japanese: 告白)
description: Fukasaku and Shima fall in battle, leaving Naruto open to be captured by Tendo Pain. Just when all is thought to be lost, Hinata, who was following the battle with her Byakugan, steps in to face Pain.

Title: "Planetary Devastation"Transcription: "Chibaku Tensei" (Japanese: 地爆天星)
description: Naruto loses himself after seeing Hinata taken out right before his eyes. His anger triggers the Nine Tails' chakra to go out of control.

Title: "The Fourth Hokage"Transcription: "Yondaime Hokage" (Japanese: 四代目火影)
description: Naruto meets Minato Namikaze, the Fourth Hokage, inside his inner world.

Title: "The Two Students"Transcription: "Futari no Deshi" (Japanese: ふたりの弟子)
description: By chance, Naruto and Sora get Asuma to coach them. Under the guidance of Asuma's iron fist, they immerse themselves in training with Wind Chakra.

Title: "Big Adventure! The Quest for the Fourth Hokage's Legacy - Part 1"Transcription: "Daibōken! Yondaime no Isan o Sagase - Zenpen" (Japanese: 大冒険! 四代目の遺産を探せ・前編)
description: The story goes back to right before the start of the final rounds of the Chunin Exam. As Naruto trains in preparation for his upcoming match, he hears Jiraiya speak of "the Fourth Hokage's legacy."

Title: "Big Adventure! The Quest for the Fourth Hokage's Legacy - Part 2"Transcription: "Daibōken! Yondaime no Isan o Sagase - Kōhen" (Japanese: 大冒険! 四代目の遺産を探せ・後編)
description: Naruto and the others take on the oncoming challenges in order to find the secret technique and break the previous record set by the Fourth Hokage. But Naruto's impulsive action leads the group into various troubles.

Title: "Meeting"Transcription: "Deai" (Japanese: 出逢い)
description: Naruto comes face to face with Nagato and Konan. Naruto, wanting to confront the problem of their hate-filled ninja world, asks to hear Nagato's side of the story before coming up with an answer.

Title: "Origin of Pain"Transcription: "Pein Tanjō" (Japanese: ペイン誕生)
description: To fulfill their dream, Nagato, Yahiko, and Konan walk through the war zone in search of Jiraiya, hoping to learn ninjutsu from him. After completing their training, the three form an organization with Yahiko as its leader.

Title: "Tale of Naruto Uzumaki"Transcription: "Uzumaki Naruto Monogatari" (Japanese: うずまきナルト物語)
description: Naruto remains silent after learning of Nagato's painful past. Nagato claims true peace cannot exist in this cursed world, dismissing Jiraiya's ideal as nothing more than wishful thinking.

Title: "Hero of the Leaf"Transcription: "Konoha no Eiyū" (Japanese: 木ノ葉の英雄)
description: Nagato, having decided to believe in Naruto's word, performs his last forbidden jutsu: Gedo Art Rinne Rebirth.

Title: "Rookie Instructor Iruka"Transcription: "Shinmai Kyōshi Iruka" (Japanese: 新米教師イルカ)
description: The Leaf Village is left in ruins in the wake of Pain's assault on the village. While cleaning through the remains of Ninja Academy, Iruka finds an old pillar and recognizes it as a memoir from Naruto's early years at the academy.

Title: "Iruka's Ordeal"Transcription: "Iruka no Shiren" (Japanese: イルカの試練)
description: Naruto spends his days competing with Sasuke, the academy's star student, only to screw up and be the laughingstock of the class. Due to the childhood trauma of losing his parents to the Nine-Tailed Fox, Iruka finds it difficult to interact with Naruto as his student.

Title: "Iruka's Decision"Transcription: "Iruka no Ketsui" (Japanese: イルカの決意)
description: Naruto takes up his classmates' dare to venture into the forest and retrieve an item from dead enemy ninja, unaware that the forest is dangerous.

Title: "Kakashi Hatake, The Jonin in Charge"Transcription: "Tantō Jōnin Hatake Kakashi" (Japanese: 担当上忍はたけカカシ)
description: An emergency council is held before the Feudal Lord of the Land of Fire. The topic is to discuss plans to rebuild the Leaf Village, and Danzo strongly urges the council to select a new Hokage to replace Tsunade.

Title: "Inari's Courage Put to the Test"Transcription: "Inari, Tamesareru Yūki" (Japanese: イナリ、試される勇気)
description: The Leaf ninja work to rebuild the Hidden Leaf Village. While helping with the restoration, Naruto and Sakura are reunited with two old friends--the carpenter Tazuna and his grandson Inari from the Land of Waves.

Title: "Naruto's School of Revenge"Transcription: "Naruto, Adauchi Shinanjuku" (Japanese: ナルト、仇討ち指南塾)
description: Team 7 stops in a town for some rest, where they encounter a man named Tsukado who is out to avenge the death of his relative.

Title: "Gaara's Bond"Transcription: "Gaara 'Kizuna'" (Japanese: 我愛羅『絆』)
description: Gaara, recalling a past mission carried out with the Leaf's Team 7, points out that the Leaf Village has Naruto with them.

Title: "Naruto: Outbreak"Transcription: "Naruto Autobureiku" (Japanese: ナルト・アウトブレイク)
description: Naruto visits Sakura, who is caring for Tsunade. Sakura recalls an incident that took place three years before, in which she collapsed from symptoms that resembled a disease caused by a mysterious virus.

Title: "Deploy! Team Tenten"Transcription: "Shutsugeki! Tenten-han" (Japanese: 出撃! テンテン班)
description: Tenten and Neji head for the Leaf Ninja Tool Research Lab to procure ninja tools necessary for rebuilding the Leaf Village.

Title: "Animal District"Transcription: "Animaru Bangaichi" (Japanese: アニマル番外地)
description: Condor, the ostrich previously captured by Team 7, now lives in a forest with baby ostriches. Since his last escape, Condor has trained himself to become a ninja ostrich.

Title: "Ah, the Medicine of Youth"Transcription: "Aa, Seishun no Kanpōgan" (Japanese: ああ、青春の漢方丸)
description: After accidentally finishing off Lee's last special youth drink, Naruto asks Guy to make more, only to learn one of its key ingredients, the Jofuku Flower, is out of stock. Naruto is determined to get the Jofuku Flower for Lee's sake.

Title: "Gutsy Master and Student: The Training"Transcription: "Dokonjō Shitei Shugyōhen" (Japanese: ド根性師弟修業編)
description: Jiraiya takes Naruto to a village in the hopes of teaching him how to counter the Sharingan's genjutsu attack.

Title: "Record of the Ninja Gutsy Master and Student"Transcription: "Dokonjō Shitei Ninpūroku" (Japanese: ド根性師弟忍風録)
description: Naruto and Jiraiya attempt to save a village from Kandachi, a former right-hand man to Hanzo of the Hidden Rain.

Title: "Sasuke's Paw Encyclopedia"Transcription: "Sasuke no Nikukyū Taizen" (Japanese: サスケの肉球大全)
description: Granny Cat requests that Sasuke and Team 7 collect the last cat paw print necessary to complete the "Paw Encyclopedia."

Title: "Naruto and the Old Soldier"Transcription: "Naruto to Rōhei" (Japanese: ナルトと老兵)
description: Naruto is assigned to a team led by jonin Hayama to patrol the north border of the Leaf Village. One of his teammates is Kosuke, an old man who has been a genin for over fifty years, earning him the title "Eternal Genin."

Title: "Kakashi Love Song"Transcription: "Kakashi Koiuta" (Japanese: カカシ恋歌)
description: A beautiful kunoichi spy named Hanare is captured for attempting to gather intel on the Hidden Leaf.

Title: "Neji Chronicles"Transcription: "Neji Gaiden" (Japanese: ネジ外伝)
description: During the Chunin Exam, Neji rests in the medical room, having lost to Naruto. Just as Tenten comes in to check up on him, they see the Leaf Village attacked by Orochimaru and his men.

Title: "The Man Who Died Twice"Transcription: "Nido Shinda Otoko" (Japanese: 二度死んだ男)
description: On his way home Naruto comes across a rock pasted with a peculiar talisman, which he tears off without thinking. That night, Naruto is surprised to find an amnesic ghost standing near his bed.

Title: "The Worst Three-Legged Race"Transcription: "Saiaku no Nininsankyaku" (Japanese: 最悪の二人三脚)
description: Team 7 is after a group of thieves who have stolen the precious Golden Statue from the Feudal Lord's sister.

Title: "Team 10's Teamwork"Transcription: "Renkei, Daijuppan" (Japanese: 連携、第十班)
description: Team 7 and Team 10 are assigned to help a village that is troubled by bandits.

Title: "Drive Towards Darkness"Transcription: "Yami e no Shissō" (Japanese: 闇への疾走)
description: Sasuke remembers meeting a young girl named Naho.

Title: "The Sixth Hokage Danzo"Transcription: "Rokudaime Hokage Danzō" (Japanese: 六代目火影ダンゾウ)
description: Naruto wants to help Karui and Omoi find their master but refuses to tell them what he knows about Sasuke.

Title: "Five Kage Summit's Eve"Transcription: "Gokage Kaidan Zen'ya" (Japanese: 五影会談前夜)
description: Karui and Omoi of the Hidden Cloud press Naruto to give information regarding Sasuke. Naruto realizes they're motivated by wanting to save their captured master, but decides he cannot sell out his friend. Instead, Naruto offers himself as a punching bag for Karui and Omoi to abuse to their hearts' content.

Title: "Enter the Five Kage!"Transcription: "Gokage Tōjō!" (Japanese: 五影登場!)
description: Kage from each nation set out to attend the Five Kage Summit.

Title: "Naruto's Plea"Transcription: "Naruto no Tangan" (Japanese: ナルトの嘆願)
description: To prevent the cycle of hatred bound to occur should Sasuke be killed, Naruto goes to the Raikage and begs him to forgive Sasuke, but the Raikage quickly dismisses the request.

Title: "Painful Decision"Transcription: "Kujū no Ketsudan" (Japanese: 苦渋の決断)
description: Mifune calls for the formation of the Allied Shinobi Forces to counter the Akatsuki and proposes the Hokage to lead them. Meanwhile, Sai reveals Naruto's actions to Sakura.

Title: "Racing Lightning"Transcription: "Hashiru Ikazuchi" (Japanese: 疾走る雷)
description: Madara, who has taken an interest in Naruto, makes a sudden appearance before Naruto and reveals the truth behind Itachi's actions. Meanwhile, the samurai learn of Sasuke and his team Taka's entry into the Land of Iron, and battle ensues between the two groups.

Title: "Sasuke's Ninja Way"Transcription: "Sasuke no Nindō" (Japanese: サスケの忍道)
description: The truth behind Itachi's actions leaves Naruto, Kakashi, and Yamato in shock. Meanwhile in the Land of Iron, Sasuke and the Raikage are fighting a battle to the death when Gaara, the Kazekage, intervenes.

Title: "Power of the Five Kage"Transcription: "Gokage no Chikara" (Japanese: 五影の実力)
description: Having blocked the combined attacks of Gaara, Temari, Kankuro, and Darui with his Susano'o, Sasuke goes after Danzo.

Title: "Declaration of War"Transcription: "Sensenfukoku" (Japanese: 宣戦布告)
description: Madara reveals the origin of the tailed beasts; the TEN TAILS.

Title: "Sakura's Feelings"Transcription: "Sakura no Omoi" (Japanese: サクラの想い)
description: The Kage respond to Madara's declaration of war by forming the Allied Shinobi Forces, with the Raikage as their leader. Meanwhile, Sakura arrives in the Land of Iron to speak with Naruto, but her confession surprises him. Elsewhere, Kisame appears before Killer Bee and his master as an unwelcome guest.

Title: "The Tailed Beast vs. The Tailless Tailed Beast"Transcription: "Bijū VS O no nai Bijū" (Japanese: 尾獣VS尾のない尾獣)
description: Killer Bee engages in a deadly battle against Kisame, who has come to capture the Eight Tails. Kisame reveals to Killer Bee that his weapon, Samehada, possesses the ability to rob and convert enemy chakra into the wielder's own strength. Now infused with more strength, Kisame shows his true power as the Tailless Tailed Beast. Elsewhere, while in pursuit of Danzo, Ao falls into Foo's deadly trap.

Title: "As One's Friend"Transcription: "Tomo to shite" (Japanese: 親友として)
description: As Sai rats out on Sakura, Naruto hyperventilates. Meanwhile, Madara and Sasuke make their assault on Danzo and his bodyguards.

Title: "Danzo's Right Arm"Transcription: "Danzō no Migiude" (Japanese: ダンゾウの右腕)
description: Kakashi races to stop Sakura from fighting Sasuke herself leading Narutoto over think the situation and pass out. Meanwhile, Sasuke battles Danzo, but there's something strange about his opponent.

Title: "The Forbidden Visual Jutsu"Transcription: "Kinjirareta Dōjutsu" (Japanese: 禁じられた瞳術)
description: Danzo's uncanny jutsu prevents Sasuke from landing a clean hit on his enemy. As Karin attempts to analyze Danzo's jutsu, Madara recognizes it as Izanagi, the Uchiha's forbidden Visual Jutsu and ultimate genjutsu technique that enables the user to control the space between fantasy and reality.

Title: "Danzo Shimura"Transcription: "Shimura Danzō" (Japanese: 志村ダンゾウ)
description: Danzo believes he's won the battle against Sasuke. Little does he realize, Sasuke placed him under genjutsu before they last exchanged blows. Not knowing his Izanagi has already expired, Danzo finds himself severely wounded and beginning to lose control over the First Hokage's cells inside of him. Still determined to survive and achieve his goal, Danzo decides to take Karin as a hostage.

Title: "Sakura's Resolve"Transcription: "Sakura no Kakugo" (Japanese: サクラの覚悟)
description: Having tracked down Sasuke's whereabouts with Kiba's nose, Sakura attempts to put her allies to sleep and carry out the task of killing Sasuke herself. As Sakura heads toward Sasuke, she begins to recollect her fond memories of Team 7.

Title: "Lost Bonds"Transcription: "Ushinawareta Kizuna" (Japanese: 失われた絆)
description: Memories from his childhood course through Naruto's mind as he rests to recover from his hyperventilation. Now realizing what it means to gain something dear and then lose it, Naruto sneaks out of the inn to follow behind Sakura and Kakashi to find Sasuke.

Title: "The Burden"Transcription: "Seōbeki Omoni" (Japanese: 背負うべき重荷)
description: Sakura tells Sasuke that she wishes to desert the village and join him. A skeptical Sasuke tells Sakura he will believe her if she can finish off Karin. When Sakura hesitates to do so, Sasuke attacks her with Chidori but is stopped by Kakashi, who has arrived in the nick of time.

Title: "Two Fates"Transcription: "Shukumei no Futari" (Japanese: 宿命のふたり)
description: Naruto reproaches Sasuke for attempting to kill Sakura. Then Sasuke reveals that he killed Danzo with his own hands. He goes on to declare his intent to purify the Uchiha Clan's name by annihilating the Hidden Leaf, whom he holds responsible for dishonoring the Uchiha Clan. Naruto, ignoring Kakashi's order to leave with Sakura, charges toward Sasuke with his Rasengan.

Title: "High-Level Shinobi"Transcription: "Ichiryū no Shinobi" (Japanese: 一流の忍)
description: After White Zetsu prevents Naruto from defeating Sasuke, Naruto throws his goal of becoming Hokage away and refuses to kill Sasuke just to end his life as a renegade.

Title: "The Infiltrator"Transcription: "Sennyūsha" (Japanese: 潜入者)
description: Killer Bee returns to the Hidden Cloud Village to the delight of Omoi and Karui. He has brought Kisame's sword, Samehada, with him. Bee believes the sword has taken a liking to him but is unaware that this is all just part of the Akatsuki's plan. Meanwhile, Sai informs the Leaf Shinobi of Danzo's fate.

Title: "The Five Great Nations Mobilize"Transcription: "Ugokidasu Taikoku" (Japanese: 動き出す大国)
description: The formation of the Allied Shinobi Forces is ratified by the Feudal Lords of the Five Great Nations. Each Kage returns to their village to prepare for the coming war. Meanwhile, Naruto has returned to the Leaf Village and asks Shikamaru to gather up his friends.

Title: "Kakashi Hatake, the Hokage"Transcription: "Hokage Hatake Kakashi" (Japanese: 火影はたけカカシ)
description: The Elder declares Kakashi Hatake as the 6th Hokage.

Title: "Prophecy of the Great Lord Elder"Transcription: "Ōgama Sennin no Yogen" (Japanese: 大ガマ仙人の予言)
description: Naruto is summoned to Mt. Myoboku to face the Great Elder. Meanwhile, Tsunade calls a meeting to discuss the inevitable war with the Akatsuki.

Title: "Storage"Transcription: "Kurairi" (Japanese: 蔵入り)
description: Anko and a group on Leaf ninja discover Madara's location. At the same time Kabuto requests partnership with Madara in the upcoming war. Madara is unable to say no. Meanwhile Naruto continues to remain in Mt. Myobuko.

Title: "The Five Kage's Decision"Transcription: "Gokage no Ketsudan" (Japanese: 五影の決断)
description: The five Kage make the decision to keep Bee and Naruto out of the war. Meanwhile, Naruto and Yamato are taken to a remote island for training.

Title: "The Young Man and the Sea"Transcription: "Seinen to Umi" (Japanese: 青年と海)
description: Naruto, Yamato, Might Guy and Aoba are ready to depart for the remote island. When suddenly, Aoba and Guy are attacked by a giant marlin.

Title: "The Ninja of Benisu"Transcription: "Benisu no Shōnin" (Japanese: 紅州の商忍)
description: Guy becomes extremely seasick resulting in a stop at a nearby island. Naruto finds Sakura, Ino and Choji who are on their own special mission.

Title: "The Cursed Ghost Ship"Transcription: "Norowareta Yūreisen" (Japanese: 呪われた幽霊船)
description: Naruto and the crew encounter a ghost ship. After boarding Naruto comes into contact with a boy called Hishaku who's shipmates were killed by a giant sea creature.

Title: "Battleship Island"Transcription: "Senkan no Shima" (Japanese: 戦艦の島)
description: Naruto's ship gets caught in a unique storm. The storm is the work of a group of savage pirates. After barely escaping their clutches, the crew wash up on an island which seems to have a devastating history.

Title: "The Forgotten Island"Transcription: "Bōkyaku no Shima" (Japanese: 忘却の島)
description: Naruto's ship is caught in another storm, when suddenly Guy is taken by a giant bird to a nearby island. After investigating the island Naruto finds that everything is a little bigger than normal.

Title: "Fight! Rock Lee!"Transcription: "Tatakae Rokku Rī!" (Japanese: 闘えロック・リー!)
description: Guy remembers a terrible incident that may ruin Rock Lee's view of him. He continues training Rock Lee but the training all seems to relate to the terrible incident.

Title: "Eat or Die! Mushrooms from Hell!"Transcription: "Kuu ka Kuwareru ka! Odoru Kinoko Jigoku" (Japanese: 食うか食われるか!踊るキノコ地獄)
description: Naruto's ship stops at a port to resupply. With no food everyone is starving. All seems fixed when Naruto purchases some Mushrooms. But that was only the start of a sudden flow of problems.

Title: "Revenge of the Shadow Clones"Transcription: "Kage no Gyakushū" (Japanese: 影の逆襲)
description: Naruto's ship is caught in another storm. This time Naruto uses his shadow clones to defend the ship from harm. After the storm, Naruto becomes his own worst enemy and his shadow clones turn on him.

Title: "The Closed Route"Transcription: "Tozasareta Kōro" (Japanese: 閉ざされた航路)
description: Naruto's ship is caught in an obstacle field of reefs and a whirlpools. Shikamaru is along for the ride and the situation helps teach him a lesson.

Title: "The Girls' Get-Together"Transcription: "Konoha no Joshikai" (Japanese: 木ノ葉の女子会)
description: Tenten gets all the girls together to reminisce. Kiba also holds a get together for the boys to reminisce. meanwhile, Tsunade meets with the Fuedal Lord.

Title: "Naruto's Imposter"Transcription: "Sanjō, Nise? Naruto" (Japanese: 参上、偽?ナルト)
description: Naruto's reputation is on the line as he is faced with a law breaking impostor claiming to be him.

Title: "Naruto's Favorite Pupil"Transcription: "Naruto no Manadeshi" (Japanese: ナルトの愛弟子)
description: Konohamaru seeking to prove himself as a powerful ninja, challenges Temari to a battle. Things heat up as Temari taunts Konohamaru.

Title: "The Kunoichi of Nadeshiko Village"Transcription: "Nadeshiko no Kunoichi" (Japanese: 撫子のくノ一)
description: Kokuyo craves leadership of a village through Shizuka's hand in marriage. Shizuka rejects his offers many times. Naruto then is forced into a battle for Shizuka's hand in marriage.

Title: "Friends You Can Count On"Transcription: "Nakama no Senaka" (Japanese: 仲間の背中)
description: Shino begins to reminisce about a mission he once took part in with Naruto, in which he learns the true meaning of friends and teammates.

Title: "Ah, My Hero Lady Tsunade!"Transcription: "Aa, Akogare no Tsunade-sama" (Japanese: ああ、憧れの綱手様)
description: Tenten reminisces about the time when she craved to be like Lady Tsunade, only finding out that all her characteristics didn't align with Tsunade's.

Title: "Sai's Day Off"Transcription: "Sai no Kyūsoku" (Japanese: サイの休息)
description: Sai is given the day off. He reminisces on his bonds with his friends, and ends up using his artistic skills to display his feeling of the the bond.

Title: "The Legendary Ino-Shika-Cho"Transcription: "Densetsu no Inoshikachō" (Japanese: 伝説の猪鹿蝶)
description: Shikamaru, Ino and Choji reminisce on their time with Kosuke Maruboshi, and their time creating the Ino-Shika-Cho technique.

Title: "Kiba's Determination"Transcription: "Kiba no Ketsui" (Japanese: キバの決意)
description: Kiba is upset at the overbearing success of Naruto and seeks out Kakashi to help him train. Kakashi summons his dogs to spar with Kiba and Akamaru. The pair retreat to a spot that Kiba knows very well.

Title: "Kakashi, My Eternal Rival!"Transcription: "Kakashi, Waga Eien no Raibaru yo" (Japanese: カカシ、我が永遠のライバルよ)
description: Guy is extremely sea sick and accidentally sends an SOS turtle to get Kakashi's help.

Title: "Naruto's Vow"Transcription: "Naruto no Chikai" (Japanese: ナルトの誓い)
description: During a stop for supplies, Naruto meets Akatsuchi and Kurotsuchi of the Hidden Stone. They are on an important mission to deliver a letter from the Tsuchikage to the Mizukage.

Title: "Land Ahoy! Is this the Paradise Island?"Transcription: "Jōriku! Rakuen no Shima?" (Japanese: 上陸! 楽園の島?)
description: Naruto finally arrives to the island and meet Killer B.

Title: "Killer Bee and Motoi"Transcription: "Kirābī to Motoi" (Japanese: キラービーとモトイ)
description: Motoi tells Naruto and Yamato a story about him and Killer B.

Title: "The Next Challenge! Naruto vs. The Nine Tails"Transcription: "Saranaru Shiren! Naruto VS Kyūbi!!" (Japanese: さらなる試練! ナルトVS九尾!!)
description: Naruto will face the Kyûbi with the guidance of Killer B, but first he needs to face his own inner hatred.

Title: "The Orange Spark"Transcription: "Orenji-iro no Kagayaki" (Japanese: オレンジ色の輝き)
description: Naruto continues his fight against the Nine-Tails and makes an unexpected encounter.

Title: "Target: Nine Tails"Transcription: "Nerawareta Kyūbi" (Japanese: 狙われた九尾)
description: With the help of his mother, Naruto fights the Nine-Tails. Then, Kushina start telling the story of the day her son was born.

Title: "The Fourth Hokage's Death Match!"Transcription: "Yondaime no Shitō!!" (Japanese: 四代目の死闘!!)
description: The story of the day Naruto was born continues: the mysterious masked ninja makes his move and chaos ensues at Konoha Village.

Title: "Thank You"Transcription: "'Arigatō'" (Japanese: 「ありがとう」)
description: The story of the day Naruto was born comes to an end: the situation at Konoha is critical and Minato is willing to do anything to save his newborn son and the village.

Title: "Battle in Paradise! Odd Beast vs. The Monster!"Transcription: "Chinjū VS Kaijin! Rakuen no Tatakai!" (Japanese: 珍獣VS怪人! 楽園の戦い!)
description: Guy arrives at the Waterfall of Truth to help Naruto with his training. Instead he encounters Kisame, who has infiltrated the island to locate Naruto and Killer Bee. Guy tries to prevent Kisame from delivering intel to the Akatsuki, and a battle ensues between the two.

Title: "The Man Named Kisame"Transcription: "Kisame to Iu Otoko" (Japanese: 鬼鮫という男)
description: Kisame's escape is prevented thanks to Guy's efforts. Aoba enters Kisame's mind to gather intel on the Akatsuki. In the process he learns about the ex-Hidden Mist ninja's bloody past.

Title: "The Angelic Herald of Death"Transcription: "Shi e Izanau Tenshi" (Japanese: 死へいざなう天使)
description: Madara appears in the Hidden Rain Village seeking the corpse of Nagato and his Rinnegan. Anticipating his arrival, Konan engages in battle to protect her beloved friends and to stop Madara's plot to bring chaos into the world.

Title: "The Bridge to Peace"Transcription: "Heiwa e no Kakehashi" (Japanese: 平和への懸け橋)
description: Konan fights Tobi (Madara).

Title: "The Super Secret S-Rank Mission"Transcription: "Doesu-kyū Gokuhi Ninmu" (Japanese: ドS級極秘任務)
description: The Leaf and Cloud ninja prepare to relocate Naruto and Bee, as the Akatsuki may already have knowledge of their location. Aoba assigns Naruto an S-rank mission to distract him from learning about their true mission: keeping the two Jinchuriki hidden from the enemy.

Title: "The Artist Returns"Transcription: "Geijutsuka Futatabi" (Japanese: 芸術家再び)
description: Kabuto and a reanimated Deidara attempt to grab hold of the jinchuriki, but are stopped by the Tsuchikage, who has come to protect Naruto.

Title: "Assemble! Allied Shinobi Forces!"Transcription: "Shūketsu! Shinobi Rengōgun!" (Japanese: 集結! 忍連合軍!)
description: The Tsuchikage and his team manage to safeguard the Jinchuriki, but at the cost of losing Yamato to the enemy. Meanwhile, both the Allied Shinobi Forces and the Akatsuki complete their final preparations for battle. The Fourth Great Ninja War is about to begin.

Title: "Meeting"Transcription: "Deai" (Japanese: 出会い)
description: A look back into the early years when Naruto and Sasuke first met and got to know each other.

Title: "Rivals"Transcription: "Raibaru" (Japanese: ライバル)
