description: During the Chunin Exam, Sasuke witnesses Naruto's growth as a shinobi and comes to acknowledge his teammate as a rival that he doesn't want to lose to.

Title: "Rift"Transcription: "Kiretsu" (Japanese: 亀裂)
description: Sasuke's defeat to Gaara, and later Itachi, forces him to realize that he is not strong enough to get revenge against his older brother. To make matters worse, his jealousy of Naruto's growth deepens Sasuke's thirst for power.

Title: "Parting"Transcription: "Ribetsu" (Japanese: 離別)
description: Naruto and Sasuke clash in battle.

Title: "For My Friend"Transcription: "Tomo no Tame ni" (Japanese: 友のために)
description: The Allied Shinobi Forces are on standby, ready to confront Madara's army of reanimated shinobi and 100,000 White Zetsu. But distrust still exists among the Allied Shinobi Forces, who were once sworn enemies until recently. To foster unity among the troops, Gaara delivers a speech about the reasons why he is fighting, and what it means for the future of all shinobi.

Title: "War Begins"Transcription: "Kaisen!" (Japanese: 開戦!)
description: Kankuro's commando unit enters enemy territory to set up a stronghold for the Allied Shinobi Forces. They are immediately ambushed by the Akatsuki's own commando unit comprised of the reanimated Deidara and Sasori. The Fourth Great Ninja War has officially begun.

Title: "Sai and Shin"Transcription: "Sai to Shin" (Japanese: サイとシン)
description: The Allied Shinobi Forces' commando unit engages with the Akatsuki in the first wave of battle. During the fight, Sai is reunited with his brother Shin who has been reanimated and is now under the Akatsuki's control.

Title: "Secrets of the Reanimation Jutsu"Transcription: "Edo Tensei no Himitsu" (Japanese: 穢土転生の秘密)
description: Under the guidance of Killer Bee, Naruto enters the final stage of training to master the Tailed Beast Bomb, a Jinchuriki's most powerful technique. Meanwhile, Kabuto agrees to divulge the secret behind the Reanimation Jutsu to Madara as a token of trust.

Title: "An Old Nemesis Returns"Transcription: "Shukuteki to no Saikai" (Japanese: 宿敵との再会)
description: The commando unit is in hot water as they engage the reanimated Kekkei Genkai shinobi, which include Zabuza Momochi and Haku. Luckily, Kakashi and his unit arrive in time to assist them. Realizing they no longer have control over their bodies, Haku and Zabuza implore Kakashi to stop them at all costs.

Title: "The First and Last Opponent"Transcription: "Saisho no Teki, Saigo no Teki" (Japanese: 最初の敵, 最後の敵)
description: Kakashi and his unit devise a strategy to take on the Kekkei Genkai shinobi, but it's foiled by Kabuto, who uses the Reanimation Jutsu to summon the most powerful members of the Seven Ninja Swordsmen of the Mist. As the battle intensifies, Kakashi is determined to bring an end to this meaningless war and free the souls of Zabuza and Haku.

Title: "The Brilliant Military Advisor of the Hidden Leaf"Transcription: "Konoha no Tensai Gunshi" (Japanese: 木ノ葉の天才軍師)
description: The Akatsuki dispatch an army of powerful reanimated shinobi and White Zetsu across the war zone, causing chaos within the Allied Shinobi Forces' chain of command. Taking the matter seriously, the Raikage plans to join the battle but is halted by Shikaku Nara, who quickly devises a strategy to deal with the situation.

Title: "Battleground!"Transcription: "Sorezore no Gekisen!!" (Japanese: それぞれの激戦!!)
description: The Feudal Lords gather at a fortified palace, and Black Zetsu arrives at the outside. Black Zetsu infiltrates the fortress but the Lords were fake and forces himself to escape from the premises and maintains his surveillance on the ground. Meanwhile at the coastline, White Zetsus and the undead ninjas start their assault. Hyuga Hizashi confronts his brother Hiashi and reiterates that his death is for the sake of the entire Hyuga clan. At the desert, orders from headquarters telling Shikamaru to assist Darui's division and Temari becomes worried as they're facing a ...

Title: "Forbidden Words"Transcription: "Enu Jī Wādo" (Japanese: NGワード)
description: Atsui, Samui, and Darui face off against Kinkaku and Ginkaku, the legendary brothers from the Hidden Cloud, feared even by the Raikage. Using the Five Treasured Tools of the Sage of Six Paths, the brothers quickly defeat Atsui and Samui, leaving Darui to fight on his own.

Title: "Golden Bonds"Transcription: "Konjiki no Kizuna" (Japanese: 金色の絆)
description: Having transformed into a pseudo-Nine-Tails in response to his brother being sealed, Kinhaku starts his rampage with Darui's division unable to content with the stronger foe despite their attempts. At the headquarters, Mabui, A's handpicked secretary, uses her object teleportation jutsu to transfer the sealing pot known as the Kohaku no Johei to Darui. Still at the coastline, the Kohaku no Johei arrives and so is the half of the Fourth Division to assist Darui's division. Darui manages to seal Kinkaku with the help of Ino-Shika-Cho. But Kakuzu arrives to face ...

Title: "Road to Sakura" (Japanese: ROAD TO SAKURA)
description: Sakura falls from a great height and gets amnesia. Ino tries to help her remember.

Title: "Mifune vs. Hanzō" (Japanese: ミフネVS半蔵)
description: As the Surprise Attack Division attempt to retreat the the rendezvous point, they are chased by Akatsuki's reinforcements. Summoning his salamander Ibuse, Hanzou orders it to attack. Unleashing a paralyzing mist of poison, the division is rendered paralyzed and left at Hanzou's mercy. However Mifune and his division soon arrive and he deflects the would-be devastating blow. Conversing about the past and the paths they had chosen to walk, as the two trade blows, Mifune is able to break Hanzou's sickle and respirator. Finally remembering his encounter with Mifune in ...

Title: "True Kindness"Transcription: "Hontō no Yasashisa" (Japanese: 本当 の優しさ)
description: Izumo and Kotetsu arrive and manage to bind Kakuzu. As they ask Ino-Shika-Cho to help seal the constrained Kakuzu, Shikaku interferes and tells them to handle Kakuzu with Darui whilst Ino-Shika-Cho confront their sensei Asuma Sarotobi. They recall their previous spar with Asuma when they're genin and Asuma lecturing Choji about his kindness. Shikamaru also recollects his past in protecting his comrades and Ino thinking about Asuma's last words which she should must guide Shikamaru and Choji. Other ninjas try to subdue Asuma but they were failed and the Ino-Shika-Cho ...

Title: "The Complete Ino-Shika-Cho Formation!"Transcription: "Kanpeki na Inoshikachō!!" (Japanese: 完璧な猪鹿蝶!!)
description: The reunion of Ino-Shika-Cho to their sensei Asuma continues as Choji somewhat loses his will to fight. Ino manages to enter Choji's mind and tells that the meaning of their earrings that Asuma gave to them years ago. After Shikamaru recalling Asuma's last words, he scolded Choji and telling that they're not the ones to be protected but to stand up and protect others. Choji continues to recollect his past, about his kindness and the oath of being the next head of the Akamichi clan, and the butterfly who started as a simple yet kind caterpillar. Filled by his resolve, ...

Title: "A Message from the Heart"Transcription: "Kokoro no Naka no Tegami" (Japanese: 心の中の手紙)
description: Naruto leaves his training hall but being blocked by shinobi guards. Aburame Shibi insists Naruto to go back but Iruka arrives and attempts to fool Naruto. However, Naruto didn't believe on Iruka and using his Sage Mode he manages to leave the cave. Naruto was restrained via a shadow jutsu and Iruka continues to convince Naruto. Iruka gives Naruto's headband which he is about to restrain Naruto, but Naruto overpowers the group and leaves. On his headband, Naruto reads the letter from Iruka telling that he should come back alive. Iruka asks Bee a favor to protect him. ...

Title: "Attack of the Gedo Statue"Transcription: "Gedō Mazō no Shūrai" (Japanese: 外道魔像の襲来)
description: With Kakashi's return, Naruto resumes training for his new jutsu. Kakashi explains that the transformation training will enter the next stage.

Title: "Unison Sign"Transcription: "Wakai no In" (Japanese: 和解の印)
description: Naruto and Nine Tails engage in a heated conversation. Nine Tails continues to berate Naruto about hatred and Sasuke's hatred. They recall Naruto's first spar with Sasuke which Naruto didn't do anything but to continue raise Sasuke's anger in Nine Tails' opinion. Naruto fully confronts Nine Tails telling him that he will manage to do something about the ensuing war, Sasuke's hatred and even Nine Tails' hatred.

Title: "Medic Ninja in Danger"Transcription: "Nerawareta Iryō Ninja" (Japanese: 狙われた医療忍者)
description: As night falls in the Ninja War, Madara's next phase with White Zetsu begins. Over at the Medical Unit camp, Sakura and the other medic ninja work nonstop to treat the wounded. Neji is there to recover from overusing his Byakugan.

Title: "White Zetsu's Trap"Transcription: "Shiro Zetsu no Torappu" (Japanese: 白ゼツの罠)
description: Kiba, Hinata and Shino get trapped in a cave that seems to act like a hole in the barrier. What really awaits them is white zestu's sinister plan to take them down and further infiltrate the camp.

Title: "Aesthetics of an Artist"Transcription: "Geijutsuka no Bigaku" (Japanese: 芸術家の美学)
description: Back at the Fifth Company's camp, Kurotsuchi attempts to negotiate with the captive Deidara to find out Kabuto's location, but is quickly rebuffed. When Deidara learns that Sasuke survived his ultimate art explosion, he plans an escape with help from a White Zetsu.

Title: "The Allied Mom Force!!"Transcription: "Kā-chan Rengōgun!!" (Japanese: 母ちゃん連合軍!!)
description: Konohamaru participates in a meeting organized by Ebisu in Konoha of the remaining villagers, mostly including the children and wives. Ebisu attempts to rally everyone's' spirits together in the event that rogue ninja should attack the village while their shinobi families are away at war, but the mothers scoff and claim that they will protect the village as they always have while their husbands fought. Suddenly Konohamaru is approached by several children, each claiming to have seen terrifying rogue ninja roaming the east and west forests outside Konoha. He tries to ...

Title: "The Secret Origin of the Ultimate Tag Team!"Transcription: "Hiwa: Saikyō Taggu!!" (Japanese: 秘話・最強タッグ!!)
description: Tsunade and the Raikage arrive to prevent Naruto and Killer Bee from joining the battle. But the two Kage fail to convince the Jinchuriki to turn back, forcing the Raikage to use extreme force.

Title: "Two Suns"Transcription: "Futatsu no Taiyō!!" (Japanese: 二つの太陽!!)
description: Fourth Raikage Ay attacks Naruto in an attempt to prevent the Jinchuriki from falling into Madara's hands. Ay is unwilling to listen to either Tsunade or Killer Bee's pleas to change his mind.

Title: "The Helmet Splitter: Jinin Akebino!"Transcription: "Kabutowari! Akebino Jinin" (Japanese: 兜割! 通草野餌人)
description: During the night, Kakashi tells his squad to take a rest but maintain their awareness. Two shinobi arrive from HQ bringing an enormous item to Kakashi and then he hands it over to Sai, with Lee assigned to be his bodyguard, to aid in sealing the reanimated ninja. Sai becomes stressful as he recalls a seal variation of his Super Beast Scroll ability that requires emotional energy that can be harmful if not in a controlled state of mind. At dawn, the reanimated ninja sprawl out and resume killing Allied ninja on the field. Among the enemies is Akebino Jinin who is being...

Title: "User of the Scorch Style: Pakura of the Sand!"Transcription: "Shakuton Tsukai! Sunagakure no Pakura" (Japanese: 灼遁使い! 砂隠れのパクラ)
description: In a flashback, the Hidden Sand Village celebrates Pakura for her victory against the Hidden Stone village. Maki, Pakura's student, wants to train with her despite being tired from the previous skirmish and Pakura praises Maki for her fighting prowess. After their sparring match, Pakura advises Maki to be strong so she can protect her loved ones and the village. Meanwhile, in a meeting of Hidden Sand officials they stress about a truce with the Hidden Mist village despite it is against in their favor and suggest Pakura to solve the issue. However, as Maki was told, ...

Title: "Things You Can't Get Back"Transcription: "Torimodosenai mono" (Japanese: 取り戻せないもの)
description: Tsunade takes the third Raikage one-on-one at Skandenberg.

Title: "One Worth Betting On"Transcription: "Kakeru ni Ataisuru mono" (Japanese: 賭けるに値する者)
description: As she listens on to the events of A and his followers ambushed by a ninja group known as the Nokizaru, Tsunade realizes the nature of the insect as a bomb with another inside A. After explaining this and having A make a promise to her, Tsunade catches and destroys a bug which had been hovering near A for some time - unbeknownst to them that the Nokizaru had been using it as a method to spy on them. Preparing to operate, Tsunade has Shizune lead the surgery while she oversaw it. Though A initially protested, believing that Tsunade should perform the surgery, the ...

Title: "Danger: Jinpachi and Kushimaru!"Transcription: "Kyōi, Jinpachi - Kushimaru Konbi!!" (Japanese: 脅威、甚八・串丸コンビ!!)
description: Kakashi races to the scene where the Seven Ninja Swordsmen Kushimaru Kuriarare and Jinpachi Munashi were last sighted.

Title: "The Lightning Blade: Ameyuri Ringo!"Transcription: "Raitō!! Ringo Ameyuri" (Japanese: 雷刀!! 林檎雨由利)
description: As Guy and Kakashi prepare to regroup their forces, they receive word that one of the units were engaged in battle with Ameyuri Ringo and decide to head to that location. Elsewhere, Ameyuri merciless attacks the members of Yurui's unit. With Yurui dead and only a handful of members left, the new leader of the team Nurui decides that they should escape as they were no match for one of the Seven Ninja Swordsmen of the Mist. As they flee, Omoi who believes that they should stand and fight, gets into an argument with Nurui and Kayui tries to quell the argument, but, Omoi ...

Title: "Power - Episode 1" (Japanese: 「力-Chikara-」episode1)
description: Taking place in the aftermath of the Kage Summit, Team Kakashi is sent out on a mission by Tsunade to a location known as "The Hole" to investigate an incident where its people were killed. Regretting that she could not assign more people to the mission because of recent incidents elsewhere, the team sets out nonetheless. While there, they split up into two teams, with Yamato and Sai encountering officers from the neighboring Hachou Village where Shiseru and her team, after learning they are from Konoha shinobi, escort them to their village leader Disonasu. Elsewhere,...

Title: "Power - Episode 2" (Japanese: 「力-Chikara-」episode2)
description: While investigating the village near Tonika, Kabuto confronts Naruto. An epic battle erupts as Kabuto uses the forbidden Reanimation Jutsu against Naruto. In the meantime, Dokku and the five survivors lie low at the village where Mina learns a particular melody that she keeps playing on the xylophone. Naruto manages to get to know Dokku and the children despite an initial misunderstanding. As they talk, he learns about the legend surrounding the Hole and the Mystic Power.

Title: "Power - Episode 3" (Japanese: 「力-Chikara-」episode3)
description: Naruto and Sakura decide to stay at Shiseru's house overnight to help watch over the survivors. Although the children cry and miss their deceased parents, Dokku and Shiseru try hard to bring everyone together as a new family. Suddenly Naruto falls gravely ill, and Mina demands that he leave at once.

Title: "Power - Episode 4" (Japanese: 「力-Chikara-」episode4)
description: A clone possessing the Nine Tails' chakra emerges from Naruto's body. Seeking more power, the clone goes on a rampage, destroying everything in its path. Will the Leaf ninja be able to stop this powerful clone?!

Title: "Power - Episode 5" (Japanese: 「力-Chikara-」episode5)
description: The Saezuri is revealed and activated. Exposing Kabuto is exposed as the true enemy, and summons the Nine-Tailed Naruto Clone, Hidan, and Deidara. Naruto and his team mates become engaged in a fierce battle.

Title: "Power - Final Episode" (Japanese: 「力-Chikara-」episode Final)
description: The Nine-Tailed Naruto Clone mutates into a hydra-tail nearly completely taking over Naruto's consciousness. Meanwhile, Dokku and Shiseru decide to sacrifice themselves to deactivate the Ama no Hoko.

Title: "Naruto Enters the Battle!"Transcription: "Naruto, Sansen!!" (Japanese: ナルト、参戦!!)
description: Naruto enters the battle to defeat the white zetsu's impostors. Naruto uses a range of new techniques.

Title: "A Father's Hope, A Mother's Love"Transcription: "Chichi no Omoi, Haha no Ai" (Japanese: 父の想い、母の愛)
description: Gaara engages the four Kage including his father. Gaara updates his father on his life. Gaara's father is in shock and chooses to test Gaara's strength.

Title: "Contact! Naruto vs. Itachi"Transcription: "Tsuini Sesshoku!! Naruto VS Itachi" (Japanese: ついに接触!! ナルトVSイタチ)
description: Nagato and Itachi meet Naruto and Killer Bee while under Kabuto's control. They are forced into battle and Itachi is able to free himself from the control of Kabuto.

Title: "The Acknowledged One"Transcription: "Mitomerareshi Mono" (Japanese: 認められし者)
description: Naruto is on the verge of losing his soul to Nagato. Killer Bee and Itachi come to his rescue.

Title: "The Mizukage, the Giant Clam, and the Mirage"Transcription: "Mizukage to Ōhamaguri to Shinkirō" (Japanese: 水影と蜃（おおはまぐり）と蜃気楼)
description: The Second Mizukage and the Third Raikage unleash havoc on the Shinobi forces. The Second Mizukage summons a giant clam that creates a mirage. Gaara faces of against Mu and the shinobi platoon fight the Second Mizukage. Naruto attacks Mu with his Planetary Rasengan. Meanwhile, the Second Mizukage argues with the platoon that they should not attack what they see him and the clam. Gaara arrives and manages to sense the location of the giant clam and Onoki delivers a powerful Earth style punch despite running low on chakra. However Onoki gets exhausted and the Second ...

Title: "Paradox"Transcription: "Mujun" (Japanese: 矛盾)
description: A viscous battle against the third Raikage begins. Can the Shinobi Forces seal one of the strongest shinobis of all time.

Title: "Terror: The Steam Imp"Transcription: "Kyōfu – Jōki Bōi" (Japanese: 恐怖・蒸危暴威（ジョウキボーイ）)
description: The battle against the Second Mizukage rages on. Elsewhere, everything has come to a standstill in the face of many White Zetsu clones infiltrating shinobi ranks, especially at the Logistical Support and Medical Divisions.

Title: "Ghosts from the Past"Transcription: "Kako no Bōrei" (Japanese: 過去の亡霊)
description: Otogakure's Sound Four is reincarnated on the battlefield. The now grown up members of the Sasuke Retrieval Team dominate their opponents. However, a seal activates around the defeated shinobi and Kiba, Akamaru, Neji, Shikamaru, and Choji.

Title: "The Underworld Transfer Jutsu"Transcription: "Yomi Tenshin no Jutsu" (Japanese: 黄泉転身（よみてんしん）の術)
description: Neji, Shikamaru, Choji, Kiba, and Akamaru arrive in another location surrounded by the sound four. Whom seem a lot stronger than before.

Title: "The Vengeful"Transcription: "Fukushūsha" (Japanese: 復讐者)
description: Time is running out for the Leaf shinobi whose souls are trapped inside the Sound Four's barrier. Ino and Shino exhaust their own chakra to keep their friends alive.

Title: "The Heart's Eye"Transcription: "Kokoro no Me" (Japanese: 心の目)
description: Hinata remembers the time that Neji protected her when they were younger, when Neji was left in charge of Hinata's training.

Title: "Fade into the Moonlight"Transcription: "Gekkō ni Kiyu" (Japanese: 月光に消ゆ)
description: Summoning a confused Hayate Gekko, who died at the time of the Chunnin exams, Kabuto pairs him up with a cloud and sound ninja and sends them into battle.

Title: "Crescent Moonlight"Transcription: "Mikazuki no Yoru" (Japanese: 三日月の夜)
description: Hayate fights against Yugao in a battle of swords.

Title: "The A-Rank Mission: Food Fight"Transcription: "Ē-Ranku Ninmu: Gozen Jiai" (Japanese: A級任務・御膳試合)
description: Naruto arrives to help a team of Allied Shinobi Forces led by Karui, who are struggling against a reanimated samurai, whom Naruto recognizes as a man named Tatewaki he met on a previous mission. A flashback entails.

Title: "The Fallen Castle"Transcription: "Rakujō" (Japanese: 落城)
description: Naruto's flashback of Tatewaki continues.

Title: "Prologue of Road to Ninja" (Japanese: PROLOGUE OF ROAD TO NINJA)
description: This episode is a Prologue to the Naruto Shippuden movie 'Road to Ninja'. It begins with Tobi speaking with Zetsu about testing out a limited, trial-version of the "Infinite Tsukuyomi".

Title: "The Old Master and the Dragon's Eye"Transcription: "Rōjin to Ryū no Me" (Japanese: 老人と龍の目)
description: Still searching thoroughly for any remaining factions of the enemy, the Third Division came across another reincarnated shinobi: Master Chen - a renown hero of Konohagakure who was thought to have died during the Third Shinobi World War.

Title: "Rain Followed by Snow, with Some Lightning"Transcription: "Ame Nochi Yuki, Tokidoki Kaminari" (Japanese: 雨のち雪, ときどき雷)
description: A young boy called Yota appears in three different places in front of the people he once knew. Yota is gifted in regards to weather abilities.

Title: "The Sad Sun Shower"Transcription: "Kanashī Tenkiame" (Japanese: 悲しい天気雨)
description: Another Yota appears in front of Naruto who suspects the one in front of him is the only real Yota.

Title: "Lingering Snow"Transcription: "Nagoriyuki" (Japanese: 名残雪)
description: The flashbacks of Yota continue until the leaf ninja finally put an end to the story of Yota.

Title: "The Reanimated Allied Forces"Transcription: "Edo Tensei Rengōgun!!" (Japanese: 穢土転生連合軍!!)
description: Kabuto summons his group of 'failed attempts' to recover his power ninja who have been sealed.

Title: "Shino vs. Torune!" (Japanese: シノVSトルネ!!)
description: Shino verses a gifted reincarnated relative from the foundation.

Title: "A Hole in the Heart: The Other Jinchuriki"Transcription: "Kokoro no Ana - Mō Hitori no Jinchūriki" (Japanese: 心の穴 もう一人の人柱力)
description: Fukai, the previous host of the eight tails, appears to fight Bee.Killer Bee is overconfident until Fukai reveals that he still has the eight tails chakra.

Title: "The Soul Living Inside the Puppet"Transcription: "Kugutsu ni Yadoru Tamashī" (Japanese: 傀儡に宿る魂)
description: The Fifth Division led by Mifune is confronted by the reanimated Kimimaro. While Kankuro fights against lady Chiyo.

Title: "Run, Omoi!"Transcription: "Hashire Omoi" (Japanese: 走れオモイ)
description: Thousands of White Zetsu overrun a group of ninja. Seven child ninja from the cloud head towards the battle as reinforcements. When Omoi hears this he runs of to find the children.

Title: "Reinforcements Arrive"Transcription: "Zōen tōchaku" (Japanese: 増援到着)
description: Naruto's Kage Bunshin finally arrives at every battlefield to help identify the White Zetsus. An unexpected and shocking surprise is revealed.

Title: "Madara Uchiha"Transcription: "Uchiha Madara" (Japanese: うちはマダラ)
description: Madara is revived through Edo Tensei, Kazekage Gaara and Tsuchikage Ônoki are forced to fight him.

Title: "The Five Kage Assemble"Transcription: "Gokage Shūketsu...!!" (Japanese: 五影集結...!!)
description: Hokage Tsunade, Raikage A and Mizukage Mei joins Kazekage Gaara and Tsuchikage Ônoki in the battlefield to fight against Edo Tensei Madara.

Title: "The Unbreakable Mask and the Shattered Bubble"Transcription: "Warenai Kamen — Wareta Shabondama" (Japanese: 割れない仮面・割れたシャボン玉)
description: Naruto and Killer B meet Tobi and the six former Jinchûriki revived through Edo Tensei. The story of how Akatsuki captured the Rokubi Jinchûriki, Utakata, is shown (filler).

Title: "Jinchūriki vs. Jinchūriki!!" (Japanese: 人柱力VS人柱力!!)
description: Naruto and Killer B fights against Tobi and the six Jinchûriki that now holds the power of the six Pain.

Title: "Four Tails, the King of Sage Monkeys"Transcription: "Yonbi — Sen'en no Ō" (Japanese: 四尾・仙猿（せんえん）の王)
description: Naruto, Killer B and the Hachibi receives aid from Kakashi and Gai to fight the Jinchûriki in biju mode. Meanwhile, Sasuke decides to go outside and test his new eyes.

Title: "Nine Tails"Transcription: "Kyūbi" (Japanese: 九尾)
description: Kurama the Kyûbi recalls his struggle to release himself from the seal through Naruto's life.

Title: "Kurama" (Japanese: 九喇嘛)
description: For years, Naruto was the target of Nine-Tails' undying hatred. But their time together has made Nine Tails understand Naruto more than anyone.

Title: "Two-Man Team"Transcription: "Tsū Man Seru" (Japanese: ツーマンセル)
description: Naruto uses up the last of his chakra trying to free the Tailed Beasts from Madara's control. When all seems lost, the Nine Tails finally acknowledges Naruto as its jinchuriki and offers its help.

Title: "The Promise of Victory"Transcription: "Shōri e no Yogen" (Japanese: 勝利への予言)
description: The tide of battle is shifting in the Allied Forces' favor, but many are uncertain that they stand a chance against Madara Uchiha. To help boost their spirits, Shikaku orders Inoichi to send out a message to every member of the forces.

Title: "Eyes That See in the Dark"Transcription: "Yami o Miru Me" (Japanese: 闇を見る眼)
description: Suigetsu finds something interesting and alongside Jûgo they go look for Sasuke. Sasuke is able to test once again his new Mangekyo Sharingan against White Zetsus and learns about the war.

Title: "A Will of Stone"Transcription: "Ishi no Ishi" (Japanese: 石の意志)
description: Tsuchikage Ônoki remembers how he inherited the Will of Stone and gather strength to fight Madara. Sasuke encounters his late brother Itachi (revived through Edo Tensei) and pursue him looking for answers. Madara reveals something that enrages Tsunade.

Title: "The Risks of the Reanimation Jutsu"Transcription: "Edo Tensei no Risuku" (Japanese: 穢土転生のリスク)
description: Tsunade leaves her post as Medic Ninja to join the other Kage in fighting Madara. Meanwhile, Sasuke goes after Itachi and learns that his brother intends on stopping Kabuto's Reanimation Jutsu alone.

Title: "Sibling Tag Team"Transcription: "Kyōdai, Taggu!!" (Japanese: 兄弟、共闘（タッグ）!!)
description: Sasuke and Itachi team up to stop Kabuto's Reanimation Jutsu. But Kabuto's new ability to use Nature Energy has made him a difficult target for the brothers to land their Susano'o attack.

Title: "To Each Their Own Leaf"Transcription: "Tagai no Konoha" (Japanese: 互いの木ノ葉)
description: Sasuke and Itachi fight Kabuto. Kabuto rememorates his early childhood.

Title: "Kabuto Yakushi"Transcription: "Yakushi Kabuto" (Japanese: 薬師カブト)
description: Yakushi Kabuto rememorates how he has become who he is now through the different events in his life.

Title: "The Izanami Activated"Transcription: "Hatsudō: Izanami" (Japanese: 発動・イザナミ)
description: Sasuke and Itachi continue their fight against Kabuto. Itachi uses the Izanami.

Title: "Izanagi and Izanami"Transcription: "Izanagi to Izanami" (Japanese: イザナギとイザナミ)
description: Itachi explains to Sasuke how the Izanami works and how it is related to the Izanagi.

Title: "I Will Love You Always"Transcription: "Omae o Zutto Aishiteiru" (Japanese: お前をずっと愛している)
description: The five Kage continue their fight against Madara Uchiha as he uses his final Susanoo and attacks them with full power. Meanwhile, Itachi says his final words to Sasuke.

Title: "Reanimation Jutsu: Release!"Transcription: "Edo Tensei: Kai" (Japanese: 穢土転生・解)
description: Thanks to Itachi, the Reanimation Jutsu is released, and all the Reanimated Shinobi are returned to their resting places. But to everyone's surprise, the real Madara still remains.

Title: "Orochimaru's Return"Transcription: "Fukkatsu!! Orochimaru" (Japanese: 復活!! 大蛇丸)
description: Suigetsu and Jugo finally catch up to Sasuke. In order to learn the truth behind the Leaf's actions, Sasuke decides to resurrect the one man who can help him find the answer-Orochimaru.

Title: "Secret of the Transportation Technique"Transcription: "Jikūkan Ninjutsu no Himitsu" (Japanese: 時空間忍術の秘密)
description: Having absorbed the chakras of all nine Tailed Beasts, the Gedo Statue begins its transformation into Ten Tails.

Title: "Who Are You?"Transcription: "Temē wa Dare da!!" (Japanese: てめーは誰だ!!)
description: Kakashi is disturbed to discover a strange connection between the masked man's Transportation Technique and his own Kamui Jutsu.

Title: "Obito and Madara"Transcription: "Obito to Madara" (Japanese: オビトとマダラ)
description: Madara has rescued a dying Obito and tells him about his plans.

Title: "I'm in Hell"Transcription: "Ore wa Jigoku ni Iru" (Japanese: オレは地獄に居る)
description: Two White Zetsu helps Obito in his rehabilitation, while they explain more about Madara's plan and bring some news regarding Rin and Kakashi.

Title: "World of Dreams"Transcription: "Yume no Sekai" (Japanese: 夢の世界)
description: Obito watches in disbelief as Kakashi kills Rin. Unable to accept the harsh reality, Obito decides to carry out Madara's dream so that he can create an ideal world where Rin still exists.

Title: "Creeping Shadow"Transcription: "Shinobiyoru Kage" (Japanese: 忍び寄る影)
description: Years ago, Yahiko, Nagato, and Konan form the Akatsuki to realize their dream of bringing peace to the Hidden Rain.

Title: "The New Akatsuki"Transcription: "Shinsei: Akatsuki" (Japanese: 新生・“暁”)
description: Danzo deliberately misleads Hanzo, telling him that the Akatsuki are attempting to sabotage the peace talks between the Hidden Rain and Stone.

Title: "A Mask That Hides The Heart"Transcription: "Kokoro o Kakusu Men" (Japanese: 心を隠す面)
description: After the end of the Third Great Ninja War, the Leaf Village is divided over who should become the next Hokage. Minato Namikaze is soon appointed as the Fourth Hokage, much to the annoyance of Danzo and Orochimaru

Title: "Minato's Death"Transcription: "Minato no Shi" (Japanese: ミナトの死)
description: Kakashi becomes part of the ANBU Black Ops, an elite team of shinobi who are under the direct command of the Fourth Hokage, Minato Namikaze.

Title: "Hashirama's Cells"Transcription: "Hashirama Saibō" (Japanese: 柱間細胞)
description: At the Foundation, Kakashi meets a boy who uses Wood Style, a jutsu that only First Hokage Hashirama was capable of using. Kakashi goes to Third Hokage Hiruzen's library to seek answers and discovers records regarding Hashirama's cells.

Title: "The Rogue Ninja Orochimaru"Transcription: "Nukenin: Orochimaru" (Japanese: 抜け忍・大蛇丸)
description: Orochimaru is forced to flee the Hidden Leaf after Third Hokage Hiruzen exposes his illegal experiments. Danzo, fearing that Orochimaru's capture would lead to the exposure of his own involvement in the experiments, sends out one of his men to help the rogue ninja.

Title: "Orochimaru's Test Subject"Transcription: "Orochimaru no Jikkentai" (Japanese: 大蛇丸の実験体)
description: While pursuing Orochimaru, Kakashi wanders into a village inhabited by the Iburi Clan, a group of people with the unique ability to turn into smoke. Kakashi is soon captured and learns that the villagers all serve under Orochimaru.

Title: "Their Own Paths"Transcription: "Sorezore no Michi" (Japanese: それぞれの道)
description: Yukimi leaves the village to see the outside world, taking "Tenzo" with her. Kakashi tries to convince the two to return so that he can set a trap to capture Orochimaru, who is after Yukimi's blood. But Yamato, who has grown attached to Yukimi, abandons his original mission to protect his friend.

Title: "The Targeted Sharingan"Transcription: "Nerawareta Sharingan" (Japanese: 狙われた写輪眼)
description: Danzo orders Tenzo to kill Kakashi and take his Sharingan. Reluctant at first, Tenzo decides to carry out his orders after learning that the Leaf Shinobi has come to be known as "Kakashi the Friend Killer."

Title: "A Shinobi of the Leaf"Transcription: "Konoha no Shinobi" (Japanese: 木ノ葉の忍)
description: After being saved by the target he was ordered to kill, Tenzo realizes that the man known as "Kakashi the Friend Killer" is someone who values the lives of his comrades more than anyone. No longer wishing to kill Kakashi, Tenzo abandons the mission and returns to the Leaf Village, fully aware that his actions will stir up Danzo's anger.

Title: "An Uchiha ANBU"Transcription: "Anbu no Uchiha" (Japanese: 暗部のうちは)
description: Itachi Uchiha is inducted into Kakashi's unit as the youngest member of the ANBU Black Ops. Itachi's father, Fugaku, is pleased, thinking this will grant the Uchiha access to exclusive, top-secret Leaf intel. But Danzo, who wants intel on the Uchiha, orders Itachi to betray his family and clan by acting as a double agent.

Title: "Coup d'État"Transcription: "Kūdetā" (Japanese: クーデター)
description: Following the aftermath of the Nine-Tails incident, many on the Leaf Council voice suspicions that the Uchiha Clan were behind this tragedy. The Uchiha are then placed under 24-hour surveillance by the ANBU, which causes further tensions to arise.

Title: "The Night of the Tragedy"Transcription: "Sangeki no Yoru" (Japanese: 惨劇の夜)
description: Kakashi visits the Uchiha District and notices that the community seems more antisocial than the last time he visited. Meanwhile Itachi finds concrete evidence regarding the Uchiha Clan's coup against the Leaf. The fateful moment is fast approaching...

Title: "Jōnin Leader"Transcription: "Tantō Jōnin" (Japanese: 担当上忍)
description: Hiruzen relieves Kakashi of his ANBU duties and assigns him a new position as a Jonin Leader. Reflecting on his past mistakes, Kakashi decides to use the same test that Minato once used to measure one's teamwork.

Title: "Team 7"Transcription: "Dainanahan" (Japanese: 第七班)
description: Hiruzen assigns Kakashi to be in charge of Naruto, Sasuke, and Sakura, three genin that bear a striking resemblance to the former Team Minato.

Title: "Kakashi's Resolve"Transcription: "Kakashi no Ketsui" (Japanese: カカシの決意)
description: Kakashi desperately tries to reach out to Obito, but his words fall on deaf ears. Obito instead accuses Kakashi of being trash, which angers Naruto, forcing him to step in and defend his Sensei.

Title: "The Allied Shinobi Forces Jutsu"Transcription: "Shinobi Rengōgun no Jutsu!" (Japanese: 忍連合軍の術!)
description: The barrier is shattered, and Ten Tails appears! With unfathomable power in its attack, it sends shock waves through the air! Kurama takes the lead and tries to go on the offensive, but is helpless against Ten Tails' immense strength. Soon both Kurama and Gyuki exhaust their chakra and fade away.

Title: "The Ties That Bind"Transcription: "Tsunagareru Mono" (Japanese: 繋がれるもの)
description: The Allied Shinobi Forces begin their onslaught against Obito and Madara. But Ten Tails suddenly transforms and hurls powerful Tailed Beast Bombs toward distant towns. One after the other, the Tailed Beast Bombs find their targets. The shinobi wonder why Ten Tails is aiming so far away as one of the bombs heads toward HQ!.

Title: "Those Who Dance in the Shadows"Transcription: "Shinobimau Mono-tachi" (Japanese: 忍び舞う者たち)
description: Naruto is overcome with grief over Neji's death, but Hinata's words restore his fighting spirit. Shikaku outlines his final strategy before he dies, in which Nine Tails will send its chakra to increase everyone's strength. United in their cause, Naruto and the shinobi set out to take on Ten Tails, determined that Neji and their comrades will not have died in vain!

Title: "The All-Knowing"Transcription: "Subete o Shiru Mono-tachi" (Japanese: 全てを知る者たち)
description: Sasuke returns to the Hidden Leaf Village seeking answers, and standing before him are First Hokage Hashirama, Second Hokage Tobirama, Third Hokage Hiruzen, and Fourth Hokage Minato, all reanimated. Sasuke asks Hiruzen for the truth about Itachi, and he questions Tobirama about the secret of the Uchiha Clan. Then Hashirama begins his story, which goes back to the feudal age, to a period before the village even existed.

Title: "Hashirama and Madara"Transcription: "Hashirama to Madara" (Japanese: 柱間とマダラ)
description: Villages did not exist when Hashirama was a child. It was during this strife-filled time that he met Madara Uchiha. The two youths talk about their hopes for the future, without revealing their true identities, and find they share the same vision...to create a ninja world where children do not have to die.

Title: "The Era of Warring States"Transcription: "Sengoku Jidai" (Japanese: 戦国時代)
description: Madara and Hashirama eventually become the leaders of their respective clans. As the fighting rages on between the Senju and Uchiha, Hashirama approaches Madara about an alliance. But Madara refuses to listen and releases Susano'o instead!

Title: "My True Dream"Transcription: "Hontō no Yume" (Japanese: 本当の夢)
description: The Senju and Uchiha clans join together to build a shinobi village and fulfill their dreams. Standing on the cliff where they confided their youthful aspirations to each other, Hashirama and Madara gaze over the forest at their burgeoning village. Hashirama decides that Madara should be the Hokage, but his younger brother Tobirama objects, warning that the Uchiha are dangerous.

Title: "Sasuke's Answer"Transcription: "Sasuke no Kotae" (Japanese: サスケの答え)
description: After listening to what Hashirama and the rest of the former Hokage have to say, Sasuke finally understands how the Leaf Village and its shinobi came to be. He then decides on the path he will ultimately take!

Title: "Hole"Transcription: "Kazaana" (Japanese: 風穴)
description: The fighting rages between Naruto, who stands at the vanguard of the Allied Shinobi Forces, and the team of Madara and Obito. Ten Tails' relentless attack is wearing down Naruto, and his chakra begins to dissipate. Meanwhile, Kakashi and Obito face each other in a different Kamui dimension.

Title: "Something to Fill the Hole"Transcription: "Umeru Mono" (Japanese: 埋めるもの)
description: Ten Tails is on the brink of its final transformation and begins to form a massive Tailed Beast Bomb. The shinobi no longer have the strength or energy left to stop it, but Sakura, Shikamaru and the others refuse to give up. Shikamaru formulates a plan to combine the strength of the shinobi to block the Tailed Beast Bomb, but it proves too powerful. Right at that moment, Minato, who was revived with the Reanimation Jutsu, comes to the rescue!

Title: "Team 7 Assemble!"Transcription: "Dainanahan, Shūketsu!!" (Japanese: 第七班、集結!!)
description: Team 7 is finally reunited when Naruto, Sakura and Sasuke join forces. Then the reanimated former Hokage arrive to add their strength to a counteroffensive. Ten Tails divides into countless parts, and Naruto and Sasuke charge at them. Refusing to be left behind, Sakura follows!

Title: "The New Three-Way Deadlock"Transcription: "Aratanaru Sansukumi" (Japanese: 新たなる三竦み)
description: Bearing a close resemblance to the Legendary Sannin, Naruto, Sakura and Sasuke make a stunning arrival on the battlefield with each of their summonings.

Title: "Kakashi vs. Obito"Transcription: "Kakashi tai Obito" (Japanese: カカシVSオビト)
description: Kakashi and Obito face again in an epic fight to give birth to a new evil.

Title: "The Directive to Take the Nine-Tails!"Transcription: "Kyūbi Gōdatsu Shirei" (Japanese: 九尾強奪指令)
description: The townspeople are going about their daily business on the streets of the Leaf Village when someone suddenly appears and starts sending them flying.

Title: "Naruto vs. Mecha Naruto"Transcription: "Naruto tai Meka Naruto" (Japanese: ナルト対メカナルト)
description: The townspeople are going about their daily business on the streets of the Leaf Village when someone suddenly appears and starts sending them flying.

Title: "The Ten Tails' Jinchuriki"Transcription: "Jūbi no Jinchūriki" (Japanese: 十尾の人柱力)
description: Obito completely absorbs the giant Ten Tails, undergoes a transformation and becomes the Ten Tails' Jinchuriki.

Title: "An Opening"Transcription: "Toppakō" (Japanese: 突破口)
description: Obito has gained complete control over his power as the Ten Tails Jinchuriki as his powerful, cold-blooded attacks force Naruto and his friends into a corner.

Title: "The Day Naruto Was Born"Transcription: "Naruto ga Umareta Hi" (Japanese: ナルトが生まれた日)
description: As Minato confronts Obito he becomes full of regret.

Title: "The Divine Tree"Transcription: "Shinju" (Japanese: 神樹)
description: Naruto and Minato combine their powers to perform a Sage Jutsu attack on Obito.

Title: "A Shinobi's Dream"Transcription: "Shinobi no Yume" (Japanese: 忍の夢)
description: The Ten Tails morphs into its final form, "The Divine Tree," and attacks the shinobi, absorbing their chakra one after another.

Title: "Pursuing Hope"Transcription: "Saki o Ou" (Japanese: 希望（さき）を追う)
description: Naruto's past, thoughts, and feelings flow into the consciousness of every shinobi, unifying their hearts.

Title: "A Heart Filled With Comrades"Transcription: "Nakama de Michita Kokoro" (Japanese: 仲間で満ちた心)
description: Naruto and Sasuke size up Obito as the final battle looms.

Title: "Obito Uchiha"Transcription: "Uchiha Obito" (Japanese: うちはオビト)
description: Naruto objects to Obito's claim that he is the second Sage of Six Paths and declares that he is Obito Uchiha.

Title: "I'm Always Watching"Transcription: "Chanto Miteru" (Japanese: ちゃんと見てる)
description: Pressed by Naruto, Obito remembers the time he, Kakashi, and Rin teamed up for the Chunin Exam and when he promised Rin that he would become Hokage.

Title: "The Promise That Was Kept"Transcription: "Mamorareta Yakusoku" (Japanese: 守られた約束)
description: Naruto's power of persuasion moves Obito's heart.

Title: "My First Friend"Transcription: "Saisho no Tomo" (Japanese: 最初の友)
description: Gaara tells the story of how Naruto and he became friends.

Title: "The Adored Elder Sister"Transcription: "Akogare no Nē-sama" (Japanese: 憧れの姉さま)
description: The Hyuga Clan, in which the side branch family exists solely to protect the main family, has a legacy of hatred and division. Hanabi adores her sister Hinata, who struggles to become a worthy successor to the Hyuga Clan.

Title: "Hanabi's Decision"Transcription: "Hanabi no Ketsui" (Japanese: ハナビの決意)
description: Hanabi begins training in order to be strong and kind like Hinata. But when Hinata is labeled unfit as a successor, Hanabi's heart becomes bound to her destiny.

Title: "Madara Uchiha Arises"Transcription: "Uchiha Madara, Tatsu" (Japanese: うちはマダラ、立つ)
description: Naruto and the Allied Shinobi Forces successfully extract the Tailed Beasts from Obito. Only Madara remains, and Naruto heads out to tackle this foe.

Title: "The Hidden Heart"Transcription: "Ura no Kokoro" (Japanese: 裏の心)
description: With his newly revived strength, Madara doesn't give in against the nine Tailed Beasts.

Title: "A True Ending"Transcription: "Hontō no Owari" (Japanese: 本当の終わり)
description: Despite all efforts, Kurama is extracted from Naruto, and ultimately, all the Tailed Beasts are imprisoned inside the Gedo Statue.

Title: "The New Chunin Exams"Transcription: "Aratanaru Chūnin Shiken" (Japanese: 新たなる中忍試験)
description: Tsunade has left Naruto's life in Sakura's hands. As she rides off with Naruto on Gara's sand to find Minato, the Fourth Hokage, the scene skips backwards to two years after Naruto left the Hidden Leaf Village to train with Master Jariaya. All of Naruto's comrades continue to be inspired by him even in his absence and train hard for his return. Amidst all of the training, the Fifth Hokage, Lady Tsunade, and the Fifth Kazekage, Gara, meet to discuss the return of the chunin exams.

Title: "The Chunin Exams Begin"Transcription: "Chūnin Shiken, Kaishi!" (Japanese: 中忍試験、開始!)
description: The Hidden Leaf begin preparing for the Chunin Exams. Tsunade orders Kakashi to personally deliver an invitation to the Hidden Rain Village and, at the same time, gather intel. The Mist, Cloud and Stone send their regrets, but the Hidden Waterfall and Hidden Grass accept. Ino and Choji ask Sakura to join their three-man team as a stand-in for Shikamaru, who is already a chunin. But Sakura is hesitant and turns them down.

Title: "The Three Questions"Transcription: "Mittsu no Mondai" (Japanese: 三つの問題)
description: The Chunin Exams finally begin and the proctor for Round One is none other than Shikamaru! The first exam is a written test. The entrants are separated from their teams, and with little explanation from Shikamaru, the exam begins. The time limit is 30 minutes and there are only three questions. As the minutes tick away, Neji remembers the last Chunin Exams where Naruto turned in a blank sheet and still passed. He begins to realize that this exam is not about measuring one's problem-solving skills!

Title: "One Worthy as a Leader"Transcription: "Rīdā ni Fusawashī Mono" (Japanese: リーダーに相応しい者)
description: The genin are unable to figure out the answer and start to panic. Neji announces to everyone in the room that he will tell them how to answer the question. Some of the genin don't agree with Neji's taking the lead and try to pick a fight, but fighting is prohibited. Those who fear elimination follow Neji's instructions, and soon the time limit is up. However, Shikamaru introduces another question to be answered within three minutes. Will Neji and his team be able to pass this round?

Title: "The Night Before the Second Exam"Transcription: "Niji Shiken, Zen'ya" (Japanese: 二次試験、前夜)
description: Kankuro tries in vain to stop Gaara from supervising the exams due to the lack of security and the threats against his life. Gaara vows to see the exams through to completion because of their significance to him as the place he first met Naruto. On the night before the Second Exam, the entrants gather in the cafeteria, and a brawl breaks out. While the Hidden Leaf stand by helpless, the only one who can calm everyone down is Fuu from the Hidden Waterfall Village.

Title: "Demon Desert Survival"Transcription: "Ma no Sabaku no Sabaibaru" (Japanese: 魔の砂漠のサバイバル)
description: The Second Exam finally begins! To pass this stage, each team must take possession of both the Heaven and Earth scrolls and make it to the designated site in the center of the Demon Desert within 72 hours. Neji, Lee, and Tenten dash out at the starting signal. After observing Shira deflect Lee's kick and Fuu's enormous power, Neji decides they must avoid any encounter with their two teams. However, Lee is eager to challenge Shira!

Title: "As a Taijutsu User"Transcription: "Taijutsu Tsukai to shite..." (Japanese: 体術使いとして...)
description: Like Lee, Shira can only use taijutsu. In the Hidden Sand, those who can't use ninjutsu cannot become shinobi. However, Lord Gaara recognizes Shira's taijutsu abilities and appoints him as his own taijutsu coach. Envious of Shira's sudden rise to prominence, the other Sand shinobi criticize and attack him. Noting the similarities of their circumstances, Lee is outraged at the ones who hurt and belittled Shira and sets out in pursuit!

Title: "The Ultimate"Transcription: "Kiwameshi mono" (Japanese: 極めし者)
description: Lee challenges Shira to a battle between taijutsu users! Although it first appears the two are evenly matched in speed and attacks, Lee's smaller physique begins to sustain damage. In order to counter this, Lee resorts to using his Eight Inner Gates, but he is unable to release the First Gate!

Title: "Escape vs. Pursuit"Transcription: "Tōsō VS Tsuigeki" (Japanese: 逃走VS追跡)
description: Kiba and his team are in pursuit of Hidden Grass Ninja who have stolen their scroll! Their foes are experts of escape and prove elusive even for Kiba and his team of expert sensory ninja. Their goal is just before them, but unless they find the enemy, the Hidden Grass will get there first!

Title: "Unwavering Gutsiness"Transcription: "Akiramenai Dokonjō" (Japanese: 諦めないド根性)
description: Kiba and his team are in pursuit of Hidden Grass Ninja who have stolen their scroll! Their foes are masters of escape and prove elusive even for Kiba and his team of expert sensory ninja. Their goal is just ahead of them, but unless they find the enemy, the Hidden Grass will get there first!

Title: "Tenten's Troubles"Transcription: "Tenten no Nayami" (Japanese: テンテンの悩み)
description: As the team prepares for dinner, Tenten pulls out a scroll that contains all the ingredients for okonomiyaki. Lee is amazed at her ability to conjure up anything and mentions that she is "convenient" to have around. Tenten takes offense and storms off. The following day, they run into Ajisai of the Hidden Rain and her team. As fighting breaks out for the scrolls, Tenten feels an intense rivalry with Ajisai, who also specializes in Transportation Ninjutsu.

Title: "The Imprisoned Pair"Transcription: "Tojikomerareta Futari" (Japanese: 閉じ込められた二人)
description: An ancient ruin in Demon Desert comes crumbling down during the battle for the scrolls. Tenten and Ajisai fall deep below the rubble. When they realize they're trapped, they call a truce in order to find a way out. While searching for an exit, they are attacked by a swarm of giant ants. Witnessing Ajisai's proficiency with the Summoning Jutsu, Tenten recalls her training with Guy.

Title: "The Place Where I Belong"Transcription: "Jibun no Ibasho" (Japanese: 自分の居場所)
description: Ino, Sakura and Choji trudge across a desert under the blazing sun without any provisions. Ino and Sakura are arguing when a giant scorpion attacks and injures Sakura. While Ino tends to Sakura's wound with Medical Ninjutsu, she remembers back to when she ducked out of her Ino-Shika-Cho training and how her intense rivalry with Sakura drove her to ask Lady Tsunade if she could become her apprentice.

Title: "The Yamanaka Clan: Secret Ninjutsu"Transcription: "Yamanaka Ichizoku – Hiden Ninjutsu" (Japanese: 山中一族・秘伝忍術)
description: As Ino and her team head toward an oasis, they are attacked by a team of Sand Shinobi comprised of Ameno, Shishio, and Kouji. Ameno is a Medical Ninja whose skills rival Sakura's. She also has a jutsu that proves difficult to counter. Kouji is a ninja who specializes in power-based attacks, like Choji. Shishio has a jutsu that enables him to disappear and stalk Team 10. Just as Ino and her teammates are pushed to the limit, Ino remembers her Yamanaka Clan training, which she once tried hard to avoid, and unleashes her Sensory Perception Jutsu!

Title: "The Cursed Puppet"Transcription: "Noroi no Ningyō" (Japanese: 呪いの人形)
description: Sakura and her team continue their trek across the desert towards the goal. Their continuous battles have depleted Sakura's chakra, so they stop to rest. Just then, they encounter a puppet manipulated by a rival team from the Sand and end up being discovered. Sakura is helpless since her chakra is not restored yet. Ino and Choji resolve to fight, but the three shinobi from the Sand prove to be too strong!

Title: "Their Backs"Transcription: "Futari no Senaka" (Japanese: 二人の背中)
description: Ino and Choji fight to protect an immobilized Sakura although they have depleted most of their chakra due to the relentless fighting. Feeling helpless, Sakura recalls how Naruto and Sasuke always protected her. Sakura realizes that she has trained with Lady Tsunade and regains her confidence that she can protect Ino and Choji. Then the team from the Hidden Sand begins their final attack against the trio. Will Sakura be able to dig deep and stand up to them?!

Title: "The Hidden Plot Set Into Motion"Transcription: "Ugokidashita Inbō" (Japanese: 動き出した陰謀)
description: Sand Jonin Fugi sneaks into the Demon Desert and creates a massive sandstorm in order to assassinate Gaara, the Fifth Kazekage. Due to the magnitude of the storm, the Second Exam is postponed for the sake of safety. Then Matsuri and the Hidden Sand team fall into quicksand! Unaware of the sinister trap, Gaara ignores everyone's warnings and sets out to rescue Matsuri's team.

Title: "The Targeted Tailed Beast"Transcription: "Nerawareta Bijū" (Japanese: 狙われた尾獣)
description: Gaara heads out to rescue Matsuri and the others but is attacked by a mysterious priest who binds him with a Chakra Chain to capture his Tailed Beast. The massive sandstorm subsides, but panic breaks out in Hidden Sand Village over Gaara's whereabouts. Meanwhile, Foo, who is also a Jinchuriki, senses that Gaara is in danger and abandons the Chunin Exams to help save him!

Title: "Neji's Judgment"Transcription: "Neji no Handan" (Japanese: ネジの判断)
description: Neji and the team come across Matsuri collapsed in the desert and find out Garra is in trouble.

Title: "Hopes Entrusted to the Future"Transcription: "Mirai ni Takusu Omoi" (Japanese: 未来に託す思い)
description: Gaara meets with Fugi, the mastermind behind the assassination attempt on his life. He confides that perhaps, after all the fear and pain he has wrought upon the Sand, he has no right to be their leader. But there are those who accept him without prejudice--the next generation. Gaara, who has never felt this more deeply than during the Chunin Exams, tells Fugi to take his life, and his life alone, without involving the young shinobi. Meanwhile, Fuu, who has learned that there is someone very much like her by the name of Naruto, sets out to meet him.

Title: "On the Brink of Death"Transcription: "Shi no Kiwa" (Japanese: 死の際)
description: After his Tailed Beast is extracted, Naruto is on the verge of dying. Sakura desperately tries to save him, but Naruto's heart gives out.

Title: "The Two Mangekyo"Transcription: "Futatsu no Mangekyō" (Japanese: 二つの万華鏡)
description: Madara has transformed into the Jinchuriki of the Ten Tails and appears before Kakashi. Kakashi and the others combine their powers to attack, but they are no match for Madara..

Title: "The Formation of Team Minato"Transcription: "Kessei: Minato Han" (Japanese: 結成・ミナト班)
description: Kakashi changes for the worse much to Obito's distress.

Title: "You'll Be My Backup"Transcription: "Omae wa Bakkuappu da" (Japanese: お前はバックアップだ)
description: Obito's story continues, while he turns a new leaf and helps the Allied Shinobi Forces.

Title: "The Blue Beast vs. Six Paths Madara"Transcription: "Aoki Mōjū VS Rikudō Madara" (Japanese: 碧き猛獣VS六道マダラ)
description: Maito Gai remembers his academy years, his father Maito Dai's lessons and encouragement and his rivalry and friendship with Kakashi Hatake. Gai prepares himself to use the dangerous technique Hachimon Tonko no Jin.

Title: "Papa's Youth"Transcription: "Papa no Seishun" (Japanese: パパの青春)
description: With his father's teachings spurring him on, Guy sets out on his final battle.

Title: "The Eight Inner Gates Formation"Transcription: "Hachimon Tonkō no Jin" (Japanese: 八門遁甲の陣)
description: Guy Sensei has unleashed the Eight Inner Gates, opening all chakra limiters placed on the body in order to achieve power ten times greater than the hokages. His opponent is Madara Uchiha, who threatens to place the world under a deep sleep by fulfilling his Infinite Tsukuyomi. Madara, only lacking his left rinnegan to achieve full Six Paths mode, has tremendous power as is shown when he survives Might Guys Eight Inner Gates Unleashed Taijutsu. During Might Guy's and Madara's battle, Naruto is visited by someone deep within his subconscious, within his inner mind. This...

Title: "The Sage of the Six Paths"Transcription: "Rikudō Sennin" (Japanese: 六道仙人)
description: Guy Sensei reaches his limits against Madara Uchiha. A new secret is unveiled to Naruto and Sasuke.

Title: "The Ones Who Will Inherit"Transcription: "Uketsugareru Mono" (Japanese: 受け継がれるもの)
description: After Naruto and Sasuke obtained the special Justus from the Sage of Six Pathes, Shippuden goes back in time all the way to Naruto's arrival at the Hidden Leaf Village after two years of training with Jaraiya. These next two episodes are meant to demonstrate the inheritance of the next generation and for who Naruto is fighting for. This flash back tells the story of Konohamaro's training as he is being taught the Rasengan by Naruto. This story plays along with the original plot and shows Konohamaro's development of his Rasengan throught time as the several events ...

Title: "Naruto's Rival"Transcription: "Naruto no Raibaru" (Japanese: ナルトのライバル)
description: After Naruto and Sasuke obtained the special Justus from the Sage of Six Pathes, Shippuden goes back in time all the way to Naruto's arrival at the Hidden Leaf Village after two years of training with Jaraiya. These next two episodes are meant to demonstrate the inheritance of the next generation and for who Naruto is fighting for. This flash back tells the story of Konohamaro's training as he is being taught the Rasengan by Naruto. This story plays along with the original plot and shows Konohamaro's development of his Rasengan throught time as the several events ...

Title: "To Rise Up"Transcription: "Tatsu" (Japanese: 立つ)
description: Naruto and Sasuke begin to fight against Madara.

Title: "The Infinite Dream"Transcription: "Mugen no Yume" (Japanese: 無限の夢)
description: Madara is after Obito's left eye, his rinnegan, which was initially Madara's to begin with. When he obtains it, new powers are revealed that change the tide and intensity of the war, which consists of Naruto, Sasuke, and Sakura fighting Madara. Amidst the wait for Madara to come back from Obito's alternate dimension, Kakashi thinks back to the formation of Team Seven and right their questions Sasuke as to what his true intentions are, but before Sasuke could give him a definitive answer, Kakashi shuts him down and Madara shows up. While keeping Team Seven occupied ...

Title: "The Infinite Tsukuyomi"Transcription: "Mugen Tsukuyomi" (Japanese: 無限月読)
description: Madara awakens the Infinite Tsukuyomi. Sasuke finds a way to protect his friends from Genjutsu. Yamato appears in the battlefield. The Infinite Dream falls upon the Shinobi World.

Title: "To the Dream World"Transcription: "Yume no Sekai e" (Japanese: 夢の世界へ)
description: Tenten falls under the Infinite Tsukuyomi and wakes up in the Hidden Leaf Village. When Lee and Guy Sensei appear, Tenten is relieved to see that she is not alone. But her joy is short-lived, as both men act oddly and are dressed stylishly-just where has she been transported to?

Title: "Where Tenten Belongs"Transcription: "Tenten no Ibasho" (Japanese: テンテンの居場所)
description: Inside the "Infinite Tsukuyomi", Tenton tries to find a way to break free of the genjutsu, while struggling with her place in the new fake world.

Title: "Killer Bee Rappuden - Part 1"Transcription: "Kirābī Rappūden - Ten no Maki" (Japanese: キラービー落風伝・天の巻)
description: Tailed beast jinchuriki's are gathering together to go up against the akatsuki after stealing most of their tailed beast powers.

Title: "Killer Bee Rappuden - Part 2"Transcription: "Kirābī Rappūden - Chi no Maki" (Japanese: キラービー落風伝・地の巻)
description: Inside the genjutsu placed by the Infinite Tsukoymi, Killer Bee has gathered all the jinchuriki in a fight against the akatsuki.

Title: "To See That Smile, Just One More Time"Transcription: "Ano Egao o Mōichido" (Japanese: あの笑顔をもう一度)
description: Karin is caught within the Infinite Tsukuyomi and dreams of her past. She was born into the Uzumaki Clan and has the unique ability to heal anyone who bites into her. Driven out of her village, the Hidden Grass takes her in, only to use her for this ability. Karin has no choice but to endure constant suffering in order to survive. She is later chosen to enter the Chunin Exams, where Sasuke saves her life. Karin has never forgotten what he did for her-or his smile.

Title: "The Loser Ninja"Transcription: "Ochikobore Shinobi" (Japanese: 落ちこぼれ忍者)
description: With the exception of Naruto's Team 7, which is protected by the Susano'o, all other shinobi have been swept into a dream world by the Infinite Tsukuyomi. Even the Hokage, Tsunade, has fallen into a dream state. She awakens to find herself in the Leaf Village, where she discovers Jiraiya's final book, entitled "Jiraiya Ninja Scrolls," and begins to read.

Title: "The Search Mission"Transcription: "Shutsugeki: Tansaku Ninmu" (Japanese: 出撃・探索任務)
description: Tsunade continues to read Jiraiya's novel. Chunin- and jonin-level ninja have gone missing, and the Fourth Hokage, Minato, orders a search mission with teams of genin led by Guy and Kurenai. Kakashi's Team 7 is also dispatched, but the hero Naruto Uzumaki, despite being the Hokage's son, has the misfortune of being labeled a loser.

Title: "Team Jiraiya"Transcription: "Chīmu Jiraiya" (Japanese: チーム・ジライヤ)
description: Tsunade continues to read Jiraiya's novel. Chunin- and jonin-level ninja have gone missing, and the Fourth Hokage, Minato, orders a search mission with teams of genin led by Guy and Kurenai. Kakashi's Team 7 is also dispatched, but the hero Naruto Uzumaki, despite being the Hokage's son, has the misfortune of being labeled a loser.

Title: "Order of Priority"Transcription: "Yūsen Jun'i" (Japanese: 優先順位)
description: Team Jiraiya, Shikamaru, and his Leaf teammates are lured into a mysterious village during their battle. A couple children from the village get caught in the crossfire and fall into a cave-in. Yahiko's team rushes to the rescue, but Shikamaru doesn't budge. Meanwhile, Naruto and Neji's teams rendezvous, but a mysterious voice addresses them out of nowhere.

Title: "The Masked Man"Transcription: "Kamen no Otoko" (Japanese: 仮面の男)
description: Naruto and Killer Bee rush to the battlefield when Nine Tails suddenly speaks to Naruto inside his mind. The Nine Tails questions Naruto's intent to end the hatred in the world and reminds him of how he was unable to save Sasuke.

Title: "The Sealed Power"Transcription: "Fūin Sareshi Chikara" (Japanese: 封印されし力)
description: The Masked Man is satisfied that the Hidden Leaf Genin chose the importance of life over their mission, but orders his team to continue their surveillance. Meanwhile, Naruto is frustrated at his inabilities, and recalls why his father Minato sealed the Nine Tails inside of him.

Title: "The Rules or a Comrade"Transcription: "Okite ka, Nakama ka" (Japanese: 掟か、仲間か)
description: Sasuke and Sakura join up with the others, but the Puppet User appears and blocks their path back to the Hidden Leaf Village. Sasuke wants to bring down the puppets and rush back to report to the Fourth Hokage, but Shikamaru and the others insist on staying and rescuing the jonin.

Title: "The Child of Prophecy"Transcription: "Yogen no Ko" (Japanese: 予言の子)
description: Jiraiya weakens the seal on the Nine Tails in order to help Naruto learn how to control the Tailed Beast's power. Jiraiya recalls the words spoken to him years ago by the Great Lord Elder. He told Jiraiya that he would have a student, and that his guidance would decide whether the student would save the Ninja World or destroy it.

Title: "The Caged Bird"Transcription: "Kago no Tori" (Japanese: 籠の鳥)
description: Naruto joins up with the rest of his comrades, and together they overcome the puppet attack. The masked man witnesses this and is convinced there is a future for the young shinobi. He promises to release the kidnapped jonin and begins to explain the truth, and the situation behind his motives.

Title: "Returning Home"Transcription: "Kikan" (Japanese: 帰還)
description: Naruto's strength is recognized by his fellow genin, except Sasuke. But while Naruto enjoys a close relationship with his father, Sasuke's father, Fugaku, constantly compares Sasuke with his older brother Itachi and barely pays attention to him.

Title: "The Mutual Path"Transcription: "Tagai no Michi" (Japanese: 互いの道)
description: Sasuke takes his frustrations out on Naruto and the two begin to fight, this time with their respective new jutsu. Minato steps in just before it turns into a disaster. From this encounter, Sasuke realizes that he is nowhere equal to Naruto in strength and joins the Leaf Police Force, determined to beat him one day.

Title: "The Difference in Power"Transcription: "Chikara no Sa" (Japanese: 力の差)
description: Three years have passed since Sasuke joined the Leaf Police Force, and he's now lieutenant. But his abusive Police Force has only increased anxiety within the village, and the Uchiha remain in poor regard. Now that his training with Jiraiya has ended, Naruto returns to Hidden Leaf Village and has an explosive encounter with Sasuke in the middle of town.

Title: "Leaving the Village"Transcription: "Sato Nuke" (Japanese: 里抜け)
description: Sasuke leaves the leaf village in search of power.

Title: "Pursuers"Transcription: "Otte" (Japanese: 追手)
description: The Anbu who attack Naruto and Shikamaru are agents sent by Danzo, who had promised Orochimaru that he would deliver Sasuke safely to him. Luckily, Neji, Lee and Tenten rush to their aid in the nick of time. Meanwhile, Hiruko reveals the truth behind the incident involving Hizashi.

Title: "Collision"Transcription: "Shōtotsu" (Japanese: 衝突)
description: Naruto reaches the tower Sasuke was heading for, thanks to Neji, Lee and Tenten deterring the agents from the Foundation. But it's too late-Sasuke's already made contact with Orochimaru. Naruto passionately tries to reason with Sasuke, but ultimately their powers collide.

Title: "Another Moon"Transcription: "Mōhitotsu no Tsuki" (Japanese: もう一つの月)
description: Naruto wakes up and is told by Shikamaru that Sasuke is no where to be found, and that the Anbu they were fighting retreated. While Tsunade updates Minato on the shinobi Sasuke attacked when he left the village, Shizune arrives with news someone infiltrated the village. Pain arrives and talks to Tsunade, vowing to cause the village pain. Pain attacks the village with a gigantic Chibaku Tensei. Naruto and the others arrive in the morning to find a crater where Konohagakure was supposed to be, with the Chibaku Tensei floating above it. Neji confirms the chakra of the ...

Title: "Comrade"Transcription: "Nakama" (Japanese: 仲間)
description: Seeing Hinata almost die triggers Naruto's anger and he goes into Nine Tails State. Naruto's power is enormous, but Pain releases his jutsu to seal him away. Hatred consumes Naruto as he tries to break the seal. With Naruto unable to calmly control the Nine Tails' power, the village steadily heads toward destruction.

Title: "The Shinobi Unite"Transcription: "Shinobitachi no Kyōen" (Japanese: 忍達の共演)
description: Several months after Pain's attack, Jiraiya arrives with intel regarding the Akatsuki, who are attacking shinobi villages and kidnapping their Kage and jonin. He also reveals that Sasuke is working with them. Naruto is determined to bring his friend and comrade Sasuke back, once and for all.

Title: "Rival"Transcription: "Raibaru" (Japanese: 好敵手（ライバル）)
description: Naruto wants to bring Sasuke back to the village, but Sasuke burns with a desire to bring Naruto down. Why is Sasuke so confrontational, and how did his feelings toward Naruto develop? The truth rises to the surface during Sasuke's relentless attack. Where will this battle lead? Find out in the conclusion of the "Jiraiya Ninja Scrolls."

Title: "Birth and Death"Transcription: "Umareru Inochi, Shinu Inochi" (Japanese: 生まれる命、死ぬ命)
description: The shinobi under Madara's Infinite Tsukuyomi continue to slumber and have pleasant dreams. Meanwhile, Naruto and the others have escaped the genjutsu, thanks to Sasuke's protective Susano'o. As Sasuke starts remembering the death of Itachi, his Sharingan starts to resonate and show him the truth that Itachi never spoke a word of.

Title: "The Genius"Transcription: "Isai" (Japanese: 異才)
description: Having experienced the Great Ninja War as a young child, Itachi constantly questions the meaning the life and death, distancing him from other children his age. Soon after entering the Academy, Itachi exhibits his genius and finds himself at the top of his class.

Title: "The Pain of Living"Transcription: "Inochi no Itami" (Japanese: 命の痛み)
description: Upon graduating from the Academy, Itachi becomes a genin and joins a team that includes Tenma, Shinko, and their Jonin Leader, Minazuki Sensei. They accept a mission from Granny Cat to look for a missing feline who's a skilled Ninja Cat.

Title: "Shisui's Request"Transcription: "Shisui no Irai" (Japanese: シスイの依頼)
description: Itachi accompanies his friend Shisui on a three-part training exercise. The two come across a battle between the Hokage's ANBU and the Foundation. Itachi is confused by their motives and can't discern which side is right or wrong. But Shisui is unwavering in his determination to stop the fighting.

Title: "Moonlit Night"Transcription: "Tsukiyo" (Japanese: 月夜)
description: Itachi joins the ANBU and is quickly promoted to captain. But he must report directly to Danzo, and is placed as a double agent to observe the Uchiha clan, who are in the midst of planning a coup d'état. With dissatisfaction rising within the clan, the Uchiha ultimately decide to carry out their revolt, and the fateful night approaches.

Title: "The Darkness of the Akatsuki"Transcription: "Akatsuki no Yami" (Japanese: 暁の闇)
description: Itachi becomes a rogue ninja and joins the Akatsuki. He is welcomed and introduced by Pain and Orochimaru as the ex-Leaf ANBU and the man who massacred his entire clan. Itachi is paired up with a man named Juzo, and their first job together is to fulfill an assassination request in the Land of Water.

Title: "Partner"Transcription: "Aibō" (Japanese: 相棒)
description: Itachi is partnered with Kisame and begins his missions as a member of the Akatsuki. The duo succeeds in recruiting Deidara, so Pain assigns the newly formed team of Deidara and Sasori to hunt down the deserter Orochimaru. Meanwhile, intel comes in about an immortal killer, so Itachi, Konan and Kakuzu head out to the Land of Steam.

Title: "Truth"Transcription: "Makoto" (Japanese: 真)
description: Itachi confronts Sasuke, who for years bore the shame and anger that Itachi brought upon their clan. The truth behind Itachi's story comes to light. Back on the battlefield of the Fourth Great Ninja War, Naruto and the others fight Madara, and just as he is declaring his victory, something unexpected occurs.

Title: "She of the Beginning"Transcription: "Hajimari no Mono" (Japanese: はじまりのもの)
description: Kaguya Otsutsuki suddenly emerges from Madara's body. She is the mother of Hagoromo, the Sage of the Six Paths who entrusted his powers to Naruto and Sasuke. Kaguya's power is immense and instantly sends Naruto and Sasuke to an alternate dimension. Naruto and Sasuke are the only ones who can seal away Kaguya, but they can't find a jutsu that works against her.

Title: "Kaguya Ōtsutsuki"Transcription: "Ōtsutsuki Kaguya" (Japanese: 大筒木カグヤ)
description: Kaguya Otsutsuki suddenly descends from the heavens as the people of the Land of Sou look on in surprise and suspicion. But their king, Tenji, is enthralled by her and takes her for his concubine. In this age of endless war, Kaguya wishes for nothing but peace. But as the self-proclaimed protector of the Divine Tree, she soon finds herself engulfed by the tides of chaos and war.

Title: "Hagoromo and Hamura"Transcription: "Hagoromo to Hamura" (Japanese: ハゴロモとハムラ)
description: As Black Zetsu drains Naruto and Sasuke's Chakra into the reborn Kaguya, Black Zetsu tells the story of Kaguya's children: Hagoromo and Hamura in a world ruled by the Infinite Tsukuyomi. Filler episode.

Title: "A Fabricated Past"Transcription: "Tsukurareta Kako" (Japanese: 造られた過去)
description: Kaguya is furious that Hagoromo has broken the law. Hagoromo finds out what Kaguya did in the past and makes up his mind to fight her. Knowing nothing about her, Hagoromo cannot trust her-he wonders if the love and the despair she experienced are the sole cause of her anger. Unable to reach an understanding, mother and sons begin their long, sad battle.

Title: "The No. 1 Most Unpredictable Ninja"Transcription: "Igai-sei Nanbāwan!" (Japanese: 意外性ナンバーワン!)
description: Naruto adopts a rather hilarious but effective approach to tackle Kaguya. Obito is back in action. Sasuke faces a challenge. The Four Hokages make an unexpected acquaintance

Title: "Ninshu: The Ninja Creed"Transcription: "Ninshū" (Japanese: 忍宗)
description: Rikudô Sen'nin tells the story of how the Ninshû was born.

Title: "Ashura and Indra"Transcription: "Ashura to Indora" (Japanese: アシュラとインドラ)
description: Tells the story of the ancestors of the uchiha and senju clan.

Title: "The Tumultuous Journey"Transcription: "Shiren no Tabi" (Japanese: 試練の旅)
description: Hagoromo must decide whom will be his successor

Title: "Ashura's Decision"Transcription: "Ashura no Ketsui" (Japanese: アシュラの決意)
description: Indra completes his mission. Asura finds the definitive solution for his village. Hagoromo must take his final decision.

Title: "The Successor"Transcription: "Kōkeisha" (Japanese: 後継者)
description: Hagoromo finally chooses who will be the successor to Ninja creed.

Title: "A Special Mission"Transcription: "Tokubetsu Ninmu" (Japanese: 特別任務)
description: Naruto, Sasuke and Sakura take on a special mission.

Title: "Connecting Thoughts"Transcription: "Tsunagaru Omoi" (Japanese: 繋がる想い)
description: The battle with Kaguya continues with an unexpected turn of events.

Title: "The Two of Them... Always"Transcription: "Futari o Chanto" (Japanese: 二人をちゃんと)
description: Obito redeems himself by sacrificing his remaining energy to save Sasuke and Sakura.

Title: "You Better..."Transcription: "Omae wa Kanarazu" (Japanese: お前は必ず)
description: Obito, sharing a common bond with Naruto over their ambitions to become Hokage, tells Naruto about his dreams.

Title: "Sharingan Again"Transcription: "Sharingan, Futatabi" (Japanese: 写輪眼、再び)
description: Obito enters Kakashi's mind and grants him power.

Title: "Congratulations"Transcription: "Omedetō" (Japanese: おめでとう)
description: The ninjas make their final move to seal Kaguya and free the Tailed Beasts, but Black Zetsu slips through in an attempt to escape defeat.

Title: "The Final Valley"Transcription: "Shūmatsu no Tani" (Japanese: 終末の谷)
description: With Kaguya's defeat, Hagomoro declares that Naruto and Sasuke can combine their power to dispel the Infinite Tsukuyomi, but Sasuke takes control of the Tailed Beasts and reveals his intention to kill the five living kage.

Title: "The Final Battle"Transcription: "Saigo no Tatakai" (Japanese: 最後の戦い)
description: Sasuke reveals his motivations as the fated final battle between two friends begins.

Title: "Naruto and Sasuke"Transcription: "Naruto to Sasuke" (Japanese: ナルトとサスケ)
description: A continuation of Naruto and Sasuke final battle.

Title: "The Unison Sign"Transcription: "Wakai no In" (Japanese: 和解の印)
description: Interrupted in the heat of battle by a blinding light, Naruto and Sasuke begin witnessing flashbacks of their childhood.

Title: "Naruto Uzumaki!"Transcription: "Uzumaki Naruto!!" (Japanese: うずまきナルト！！)
description: Sakura tends to the wounded Naruto and Sasuke as the tree finally collapses and frees the people of the world; The ninja of Leaf Village begins the long process of recovery after the war; Naruto has a heart-to-heart talk with Iruka.

Title: "Naruto and Hinata" (Japanese: NARUTO・HINATA)
description: Ostracized due to the Nine Tails that lives within him, young Naruto leads a solitary life in Leaf Village, until a stranger appears; Hinata celebrates her third birthday and meets Neji.

Title: "Sasuke and Sakura" (Japanese: SASUKE・SAKURA)
description: Young Sasuke wants to spend more time with his brother, Itachi; a reclusive Sakura receives a present from Ino.

Title: "Gaara and Shikamaru" (Japanese: GAARA・SHIKAMARU)
description: A motherless Gaara grows up under the eye of his uncle, Yashamaru; Shikamaru pranks Choji.

Title: "Jiraiya and Kakashi" (Japanese: JIRAIYA・KAKASHI)
description: Young Jiraiya ropes Orochimaru into his plans to get Tsunade to notice him; Rin and Obito try to get to know orphaned loner Kakashi.

Title: "The Exploding Human"Transcription: "Kibaku Ningen" (Japanese: 起爆人間)
description: Sasuke begins a journey of atonement following the Fourth Great Ninja War; Kakashi, Naruto and Sakura discuss a series of disappearances in Leaf Village; The village fends off a group of possessed attackers who explode when wounded.

Title: "Coliseum"Transcription: "Koroshiamu" (Japanese: 闘技場（コロシアム）)
description: Sasuke, Chino and Nowaki search for clues about the exploding humans who attacked Leaf Village.

Title: "Fūshin" (Japanese: 風心（フウシン）)
description: Continuing his investigation, Sasuke follows Orochimaru to the Coliseum to stage a fight and draw out a potential informant, but a sudden attack by more exploding humans derails the plan.

Title: "The Ketsuryūgan"Transcription: "Ketsuryūgan" (Japanese: 血龍眼)
description: After Sasuke fails to capture Fushin, he regroups with Chino at Hell Valley and learns how she came to be associated with Fushin.

Title: "The Last One"Transcription: "Saigo no Hitori" (Japanese: 最後の一人)
description: Sasuke's search for the source of the recent troubles draws toward its conclusion.

Title: "The State of Affairs"Transcription: "Fūun" (Japanese: 風雲)
description: Two years after the Fourth Great Ninja War, Shikamaru works as a Leaf Village representative undertaking an investigation into numerous disappearances.

Title: "Dark Clouds"Transcription: "An'un" (Japanese: 暗雲)
description: Sai, investigating the Land of Silence, sends a cryptic message back to Leaf Village; Shikamaru decides to head for the Land of Silence with Soku and Ro, but the team must pass through a heavily guarded checkpoint first.

Title: "Recklessness"Transcription: "Yamikumo" (Japanese: 闇雲)
description: Shikamaru and his team approach Fushu Castle, learning that Gengo will make a public appearance, they infiltrate the square, where they see Sai being held captive.

Title: "Cloud of Suspicion"Transcription: "Giun" (Japanese: 疑雲)
description: Shikamaru is captured while trying to save Sai and stop Gengo. Far from giving up, he racks his brain to find a away out of the situation. Just as an opportunity presents itself, Ro and Soku appear under Gengo's control.

Title: "Dawn"Transcription: "Shinonome" (Japanese: 東雲)
description: Ino, Choji, and Temari rush to Shikamaru's aid. Choji takes on Ro, Temari goes after Soku, and Ino goes after Sai. Meanwhile, Shikamaru pursues Gengo. Can Shikamaru defeat Gengo's evil ambitions? The final battle begins.

Title: "Naruto's Wedding"Transcription: "Naruto no Kekkon" (Japanese: ナルトの結婚)
description: As Naruto and Hinata's wedding day approaches, Kakashi encounters a problem -- if all of Naruto's elite ninja friends attend, the village will be left undefended.

Title: "A Full-Powered Wedding Gift"Transcription: "Furupawā Kekkon Iwai" (Japanese: フルパワー結婚祝い)
description: As Kakashi tries to find the most reasonable solution to the wedding guest problem, he announces a super-secret mission to find Naruto and Hinata a wedding gift.

Title: "Steam and Food Pills"Transcription: "Yukemuri to Hyōrōgan" (Japanese: 湯けむりと兵糧丸)
description: The game of finding gift for naruto's wedding is still fierce. Shikamaru along with Temari and Choji, Ino, Sakura search for the perfect gift.

Title: "The Kazekage's Wedding Gift"Transcription: "Kazekage no Oiwai" (Japanese: 風影の御祝)
description: The Tsuchikage and Raikage come to Leaf Village to attend the Five Kage Summit and prepare wedding gifts for Naruto; Gaara finds himself in a dilemma.

Title: "The Last Mission"Transcription: "Saigo no Ninmu" (Japanese: 最後の任務)
description: Kiba makes it his goal to become the next Hokage; Shino faces doubts about his own goal and sets out with Kiba and Akamaru on their final mission as Team 8.

Title: "The Outcome of the Secret Mission"Transcription: "Gokuhi Ninmu no Yukue" (Japanese: 極秘任務の行方)
description: As the wedding day approaches, each of Naruto's friends readies a gift, but no one expects their mission's true purpose - the gifts will be judged to select who can attend the wedding reception; Kakashi begins to doubt the plan.

Title: "The Message"Transcription: "Iwai no Kotoba" (Japanese: 祝いの言葉)
description: The day of the wedding finally arrives, as Iruka finally figures out the perfect message.
